obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12721)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12721&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Juvenile`
  line `Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2015.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply to all matters concerning children in need of care and protection and children in`
  line `conflict with law, including --`
  line
  line `(i) apprehension, detention, prosecution, penalty or imprisonment, rehabilitation and social`
  line `re-integration of children in conflict with law;`
  line
  line `(ii) procedures and decisions or orders relating to rehabilitation, adoption, re-integration, and`
  line `restoration of children in need of care and protection.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
  line
  line `2. 15th January, 2016, vide notification No. S.O. 110(E), dated 12th January, 2016, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12722)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12722&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(1) "abandoned child" means a child deserted by his biological or adoptive parents or guardians,`
  line `who has been declared as abandoned by the Committee after due inquiry;`
  line
  line `(2) "adoption" means the process through which the adopted child is permanently separated from`
  line `his biological parents and becomes the lawful child of his adoptive parents with all the rights,`
  line `privileges and responsibilities that are attached to a biological child;`
  line
  line `(3) "adoption regulations" means the regulations framed by the Authority and notified by the`
  line `Central Government in respect of adoption;`
  line
  line ^1******
  line
  line `(5) "aftercare" means making provision of support, financial or otherwise, to persons, who have`
  line `completed the age of eighteen years but have not completed the age of twenty-one years, and have`
  line `left any institutional care to join the mainstream of the society;`
  line
  line `(6) "authorised foreign adoption agency" means a foreign social or child welfare agency that is`
  line `authorised by the Central Adoption Resource Authority on the recommendation of their Central`
  line `Authority or Government department of that country for sponsoring the application of non-resident`
  line `Indian or overseas citizen of India or persons of Indian origin or foreign prospective adoptive parents`
  line `for adoption of a child from India;`
  line
  line `(7) "Authority" means the Central Adoption Resource Authority constituted under section 68;`
  line
  line `(8) "begging" means---`
  line
  line `(i) soliciting or receiving alms in a public place or entering into any private premises for the`
  line `purpose of soliciting or receiving alms, under any pretence;`
  line
  line `(ii) exposing or exhibiting with the object of obtaining or extorting alms, any sore, wound,`
  line `injury, deformity or disease, whether of himself or of any other person or of an animal;`
  line
  line `(9) "best interest of child" means the basis for any decision taken regarding the child, to ensure`
  line `fulfilment of his basic rights and needs, identity, social well-being and physical, emotional and`
  line `intellectual development;`
  line
  line `(10) "Board" means a Juvenile Justice Board constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(11) "Central Authority" means the Government department recognised as such under the Hague`
  line `Convention on Protection of Children and Cooperation in Inter-country Adoption (1993);`
  line
  line `(12) "child" means a person who has not completed eighteen years of age;`
  line
  line `(13) "child" in conflict with law means a child who is alleged or found to have committed an`
  line `offence and who has not completed eighteen years of age on the date of commission of such offence;`
  line
  line `(14) "child in need of care and protection" means a child---`
  line
  line `(i) who is found without any home or settled place of abode and without any ostensible`
  line `means of subsistence; or`
  line
  line `(ii) who is found working in contravention of ^2[the provisions of this Act or] labour laws for the time being in force or is`
  line `found begging, or living on the street; or`
  line
  line `(iii) who resides with a person (whether a guardian of the child or not) and such person---`
  line
  line `(a) has injured, exploited, abused or neglected the child or has violated any other law for`
  line `the time being in force meant for the protection of child; or`
  line
  line `(b) has threatened to kill, injure, exploit or abuse the child and there is a reasonable`
  line `likelihood of the threat being carried out; or`
  line
  line `(c) has killed, abused, neglected or exploited some other child or children and there is a`
  line `reasonable likelihood of the child in question being killed, abused, exploited or neglected by`
  line `that person; or`
  line
  line `(iv) who is mentally ill or mentally or physically challenged or suffering from terminal or`
  line `incurable disease, having no one to support or look after or having parents or guardians unfit to`
  line `take care, if found so by the Board or the Committee; or`
  line
  line `(v) who has a parent or guardian and such parent or guardian is found to be unfit or`
  line `incapacitated, by the Committee or the Board, to care for and protect the safety and well-being of`
  line `the child; or`
  line
  line `^3[(vi) who does not have parents and no one is willing to take care of and protect or who is`
  line `abandoned or surrendered;]`
  line
  line `(vii) who is missing or run away child, or whose parents cannot be found after making`
  line `reasonable inquiry in such manner as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(viii) who has been or is being or is likely to be abused, tortured or exploited for the purpose`
  line `of sexual abuse or illegal acts; or`
  line
  line `(ix) who is found vulnerable and ^4[has been or is being or is likely to be] inducted into drug abuse or trafficking; or`
  line
  line `(x) who is being or is likely to be abused for unconscionable gains; or`
  line
  line `(xi) who is victim of or affected by any armed conflict, civil unrest or natural calamity; or`
  line
  line `(xii) who is at imminent risk of marriage before attaining the age of marriage and whose`
  line `parents, family members, guardian and any other persons are likely to be responsible for`
  line `solemnisation of such marriage;`
  line
  line `(15) "child friendly" means any behaviour, conduct, practice, process, attitude, environment or`
  line `treatment that is humane, considerate and in the best interest of the child;`
  line
  line `(16) "child legally free for adoption" means a child declared as such by the Committee after`
  line `making due inquiry under section 38;`
  line
  line `(17) "Child Welfare Officer" means an officer attached to a ^5[has been or is being or is likely to be] for carrying out the`
  line `directions given by the Committee or, as the case may be, the Board with such responsibility as may`
  line `be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(18) "Child Welfare Police Officer" means an officer designated as such under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 107;`
  line
  line `(19) "Children's Home" means a Children's Home, established or maintained, in every district or`
  line `group of districts, by the State Government, either by itself, or through a voluntary or`
  line `non-governmental organisation, and is registered as such for the purposes specified in section 50;`
  line
  line `(20) "Children's Court" means a court established under the Commissions for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006) or a Special Court under the Protection of Children from Sexual`
  line `Offences Act, 2012 (32 of 2012), wherever existing and where such courts have not been designated,`
  line `the Court of Sessions having jurisdiction to try offences under the Act;`
  line
  line `(21) "child care institution" means Children Home, open shelter, observation home, special home,`
  line `place of safety, Specialised Adoption Agency and a fit facility recognised under this Act for`
  line `providing care and protection to children, who are in need of such services;`
  line
  line `(22) "Committee" means Child Welfare Committee constituted under section 27;`
  line
  line `(23) "court" means a civil court, which has jurisdiction in matters of adoption and guardianship`
  line `and may include the District Court, Family Court and City Civil Courts;`
  line
  line `(24) "corporal punishment" means the subjecting of a child by any person to physical punishment`
  line `that involves the deliberate infliction of pain as retribution for an offence, or for the purpose of`
  line `disciplining or reforming the child;`
  line
  line `(25) "childline services" means a twenty-four hours emergency outreach service for children in`
  line `crisis which links them to emergency or long-term care and rehabilitation service;`
  line
  line `(26) "District Child Protection Unit" means a Child Protection Unit for a District, established by`
  line `the State Government under section 106, ^6[which shall function under the supervision of the District`
  line `Magistrate] to ensure the implementation of this`
  line `Act and other child protection measures in the district;`
  line
  line `^7[(26-A) "District Magistrate" includes Additional District Magistrate of the District;]`
  line
  line `(27) "fit facility" means a facility being run by a governmental organisation or a registered`
  line `voluntary or non-governmental organisation, prepared to temporarily own the responsibility of a`
  line `particular child for a specific purpose, and such facility is recognised as fit for the said purpose, by`
  line `the Committee, as the case may be, or the Board, under sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(28) "fit person" means any person, prepared to own the responsibility of a child, for a specific`
  line `purpose, and such person is identified after inquiry made in this behalf and recognised as fit for the`
  line `said purpose, by the Committee or, as the case may be, the Board, to receive and take care of the`
  line child;
  line
  line `(29) "foster care" means placement of a child, by the Committee for the purpose of alternate care`
  line `in the domestic environment of a family, other than the childs biological family, that has been`
  line `selected, qualified, approved and supervised for providing such care;`
  line
  line `(30) "foster family" means a family found suitable by the District Child Protection Unit to keep`
  line `children in foster care under section 44;`
  line
  line `(31) "guardian" in relation to a child, means his natural guardian or any other person having, in`
  line `the opinion of the Committee or, as the case may be, the Board, the actual charge of the child, and`
  line `recognised by the Committee or, as the case may be, the Board as a guardian in the course of`
  line proceedings;
  line
  line `(32) "group foster care" means a family like care facility for children in need of care and`
  line `protection who are without parental care, aiming on providing personalised care and fostering a sense`
  line `of belonging and identity, through family like and community based solutions;`
  line
  line `(33) "heinous offences" includes the offences for which the minimum punishment under the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or any other law for the time being in force is imprisonment for seven`
  line `years or more;`
  line
  line `(34) "inter-country adoption" means adoption of a child from India by non-resident Indian or by a`
  line `person of Indian origin or by a foreigner;`
  line
  line `(35) "juvenile" means a child below the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `(36) "narcotic drug" and "psychotropic substance" shall have the meanings, respectively,`
  line `assigned to them in the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985);`
  line
  line `(37) "no objection certificate" for inter-country adoption means a certificate issued by the Central`
  line `Adoption Resource Authority for the said purpose;`
  line
  line `(38) "non-resident Indian" means a person who holds an Indian passport and is presently residing`
  line `abroad for more than one year;`
  line
  line `(39) "notification" means the notification published in the Official Gazette of India, or as the case`
  line `may be, in the Gazette of a State, and the expression notify shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(40) "observation home" means an observation home established and maintained in every district`
  line `or group of districts by a State Government, either by itself, or through a voluntary or`
  line `non-governmental organisation, and is registered as such, for the purposes specified in sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 47;`
  line
  line `(41) "open shelter" means a facility for children, established and maintained by the State`
  line `Government, either by itself, or through a voluntary or non-governmental organisation under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 43, and registered as such, for the purposes specified in that section;`
  line
  line `(42) "orphan" means a child---`
  line
  line `(i) who is without biological or adoptive parents or legal guardian; or`
  line
  line `(ii) whose legal guardian is not willing to take, or capable of taking care of the child;`
  line
  line `(43) "overseas citizen of India" means a person registered as such under the Citizenship`
  line `Act, 1955 (57 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(44) "person of Indian origin" means a person, any of whose lineal ancestors is or was an Indian`
  line `national, and who is presently holding a Person of Indian Origin Card issued by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(45) "petty offences" includes the offences for which the maximum punishment under the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860) or any other law for the time being in force is imprisonment up to three`
  line years;
  line
  line `(46) "place of safety" means any place or institution, not being a police lockup or jail, established`
  line `separately or attached to an observation home or a special home, as the case may be, ^8[***] to receive and take care of the children alleged or found to be in conflict`
  line `with law, by an order of the Board or the Childrens Court, both during inquiry and ongoing`
  line `rehabilitation after having been found guilty for a period and purpose as specified in the order;`
  line
  line `(47) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(48) "probation officer" means an officer appointed by the State Government as a probation`
  line `officer under the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958) or the Legal-cum-Probation Officer`
  line `appointed by the State Government under District Child Protection Unit;`
  line
  line `(49) "prospective adoptive parents" means a person or persons eligible to adopt a child as per the`
  line `provisions of section 57;`
  line
  line `(50) "public place" shall have the same meaning assigned to it in the Immoral Traffic`
  line `(Prevention) Act, 1956 (104 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(51) "registered", with reference to child care institutions or agencies or facilities managed by the`
  line `State Government, or a voluntary or non-governmental organisation, means observation homes,`
  line `special homes, place of safety, childrens homes, open shelters or Specialised Adoption Agency or fit`
  line `facility or any other institution that may come up in response to a particular need or agencies or`
  line `facilities authorised and registered under section 41, for providing residential care to children, on a`
  line `short-term or long-term basis;`
  line
  line `(52) "relative", in relation to a child for the purpose of adoption under this Act, means a paternal`
  line `uncle or aunt, or a maternal uncle or aunt, or paternal grandparent or maternal grandparent;`
  line
  line `(53) "State Agency" means the State Adoption Resource Agency set up by the State Government`
  line `for dealing with adoption and related matters under section 67;`
  line
  line `^9[(54) "serious offences" includes the offences for which the punishment under the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860) or any other law for the time being in force, is,---`
  line
  line `(a) minimum imprisonment for a term more than three years and not exceeding seven years;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) maximum imprisonment for a term more than seven years but no minimum imprisonment`
  line `or minimum imprisonment of less than seven years is provided.]`
  line
  line `(55) "special juvenile police unit" means a unit of the police force of a district or city or, as the`
  line `case may be, any other police unit like railway police, dealing with children and designated as such`
  line `for handling children under section 107;`
  line
  line `(56) "special home" means an institution established by a State Government or by a voluntary or`
  line `non-governmental organisation, registered under section 48, for housing and providing rehabilitative`
  line `services to children in conflict with law, who are found, through inquiry, to have committed an`
  line `offence and are sent to such institution by an order of the Board;`
  line
  line `(57) "Specialised Adoption Agency" means an institution established by the State Government or`
  line `by a voluntary or non-governmental organisation and recognised under section 65, for housing`
  line `orphans, abandoned and surrendered children, placed there by order of the Committee, for the`
  line `purpose of adoption;`
  line
  line `(58) "sponsorship" means provision of supplementary support, financial or otherwise, to the`
  line `families to meet the medical, educational and developmental needs of the child;`
  line
  line `(59) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator of that Union`
  line `territory appointed by the President under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(60) "surrendered child" means a child, who is relinquished by the parent or guardian to the`
  line `Committee, on account of physical, emotional and social factors beyond their control, and declared as`
  line `such by the Committee;`
  line
  line `(61) all words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in other Acts shall`
  line `have the meanings respectively assigned to them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause 4 omitted by Act 23 of 2021 s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for sub-clause (vi) (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "is likely to be" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2,ibid., for "Childrens Home" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "which is the focal point" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 2, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `8. The words "the person in-charge of which is willing" omitted by, s. 2 ibid., (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (54) (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12723)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `General principles to be followed in administration of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 3, for "the Board, and" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12723&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government, the State`
  line `Governments, ^1[the Board, the Committee, or] other agencies, as the case may be, while implementing the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall be guided by the following fundamental principles, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) Principle of presumption of innocence: Any child shall be presumed to be an innocent of any mala fide or criminal intent up to the age of eighteen years.`
  line
  line `(ii) Principle of dignity and worth: All human beings shall be treated with equal dignity and rights.`
  line
  line `(iii) Principle of participation: Every child shall have a right to be heard and to participate in all processes and decisions affecting his interest and the childs views shall be taken into consideration with due regard to the age and maturity of the child.`
  line
  line `(iv) Principle of best interest: All decisions regarding the child shall be based on the primary consideration that they are in the best interest of the child and to help the child to develop full potential.`
  line
  line `(v) Principle of family responsibility: The primary responsibility of care, nurture and protection of the child shall be that of the biological family or adoptive or foster parents, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(vi) Principle of safety: All measures shall be taken to ensure that the child is safe and is not subjected to any harm, abuse or maltreatment while in contact with the care and protection system, and thereafter.`
  line
  line `(vii) Positive measures: All resources are to be mobilised including those of family and community, for promoting the well-being, facilitating development of identity and providing an inclusive and enabling environment, to reduce vulnerabilities of children and the need for intervention under this Act.`
  line
  line `(viii) Principle of non-stigmatising semantics: Adversarial or accusatory words are not to be used in the processes pertaining to a child.`
  line
  line `(ix) Principle of non-waiver of rights: No waiver of any of the right of the child is permissible or valid, whether sought by the child or person acting on behalf of the child, or a Board or a Committee and any non-exercise of a fundamental right shall not amount to waiver.`
  line
  line `(x) Principle of equality and non-discrimination: There shall be no discrimination against a child on any grounds including sex, caste, ethnicity, place of birth, disability and equality of access, opportunity and treatment shall be provided to every child.`
  line
  line `(xi) Principle of right to privacy and confidentiality: Every child shall have a right to protection of his privacy and confidentiality, by all means and throughout the judicial process.`
  line
  line `(xii) Principle of institutionalisation as a measure of last resort: A child shall be placed in institutional care as a step of last resort after making a reasonable inquiry.`
  line
  line `(xiii) Principle of repatriation and restoration: Every child in the juvenile justice system shall have the right to be re-united with his family at the earliest and to be restored to the same socio-economic and cultural status that he was in, before coming under the purview of this Act, unless such restoration and repatriation is not in his best interest.`
  line
  line `(xiv) Principle of fresh start: All past records of any child under the Juvenile Justice system should be erased except in special circumstances..`
  line
  line `(xv) Principle of diversion: Measures for dealing with children in conflict with law without resorting to judicial proceedings shall be promoted unless it is in the best interest of the child or the society as a whole.`
  line
  line `(xvi) Principles of natural justice: Basic procedural standards of fairness shall be adhered to, including the right to a fair hearing, rule against bias and the right to review, by all persons or bodies, acting in a judicial capacity under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12724)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Juvenile Justice Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 4, for "less than" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12724&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the State Government shall, constitute for every district, one or more`
  line `Juvenile Justice Boards for exercising the powers and discharging its functions relating to children in`
  line `conflict with law under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A Board shall consist of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of First Class not`
  line `being Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or Chief Judicial Magistrate (hereinafter referred to as Principal`
  line `Magistrate) with at least three years experience and two social workers selected in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, of whom at least one shall be a woman, forming a Bench and every such Bench shall have the`
  line `powers conferred by the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) on a Metropolitan Magistrate or,`
  line `as the case may be, a Judicial Magistrate of First Class.`
  line
  line `(3) No social worker shall be appointed as a member of the Board unless such person has been`
  line `actively involved in health, education, or welfare activities pertaining to children for atleast seven years or`
  line `a practicing professional with a degree in child psychology, psychiatry, sociology or law.`
  line
  line `(4) No person shall be eligible for selection as a member of the Board, if he--`
  line
  line `(i) has any past record of violation of human rights or child rights;`
  line
  line `(ii) has been convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude, and such conviction has not been`
  line `reversed or has not been granted full pardon in respect of such offence;`
  line
  line `(iii) has been removed or dismissed from service of the Central Government or a State`
  line `Government or an undertaking or corporation owned or controlled by the Central Government or a`
  line `State Government;`
  line
  line `(iv) has ever indulged in child abuse or employment of child labour or any other violation of`
  line `human rights or immoral act.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Government shall ensure that induction training and sensitisation of all members`
  line `including Principal Magistrate of the Board on care, protection, rehabilitation, legal provisions and justice`
  line `for children, as may be prescribed, is provided within a period of sixty days from the date of appointment.`
  line
  line `(6) The term of office of the members of the Board and the manner in which such member may resign`
  line `shall be such, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The appointment of any member of the Board, except the Principal Magistrate, may be terminated`
  line `after holding an inquiry by the State Government, if he--`
  line
  line `(i) has been found guilty of misuse of power vested under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(ii) fails to attend the proceedings of the Board consecutively for three months without any valid`
  line `reason; or`
  line
  line `(iii) fails to attend ^1[minimum] three-fourths of the sittings in a year; or`
  line
  line `(iv) becomes ineligible under sub-section (4) during his term as a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12725)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Placement of person, who cease to be a child during process of inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12725&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where an inquiry has`
  line `been initiated in respect of any child under this Act, and during the course of such inquiry, the child`
  line `completes the age of eighteen years, then, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, the inquiry may be continued by the Board and orders may be passed in`
  line `respect of such person as if such person had continued to be a child.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12726)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Placement of persons, who committed an offence, when person was below the age of eighteen years.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12726&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, who has completed eighteen years of age, and is apprehended for committing an`
  line `offence when he was below the age of eighteen years, then, such person shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this section, be treated as a child during the process of inquiry.`
  line
  line `(2) The person referred to in sub-section (1), if not released on bail by the Board shall be placed in a`
  line `place of safety during the process of inquiry.`
  line
  line `(3) The person referred to in sub-section (1) shall be treated as per the procedure specified under the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12727)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Procedure in relation to Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12727&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such times and shall observe such`
  line `rules in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings, as may be prescribed and shall ensure that all`
  line `procedures are child friendly and that the venue is not intimidating to the child and does not resemble as`
  line `regular courts.`
  line
  line `(2) A child in conflict with law may be produced before an individual member of the Board, when the`
  line `Board is not in sitting.`
  line
  line `(3) A Board may act notwithstanding the absence of any member of the Board, and no order passed`
  line `by the Board shall be invalid by the reason only of the absence of any member during any stage of`
  line `proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided that there shall be atleast two members including the Principal Magistrate present at the time`
  line `of final disposal of the case or in making an order under sub-section (3) of section 18.`
  line
  line `(4) In the event of any difference of opinion among the members of the Board in the interim or final`
  line `disposal, the opinion of the majority shall prevail, but where there is no such majority, the opinion of the`
  line `Principal Magistrate, shall prevail.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12728)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers, functions and responsibilities of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 5, for "of such a child to the observation home" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12728&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force but save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, the Board`
  line `constituted for any district shall have the power to deal exclusively with all the proceedings under this`
  line `Act, relating to children in conflict with law, in the area of jurisdiction of such Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers conferred on the Board by or under this Act may also be exercised by the High Court`
  line `and the Childrens Court, when the proceedings come before them under section 19 or in appeal, revision`
  line `or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(3) The functions and responsibilities of the Board shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) ensuring the informed participation of the child and the parent or guardian, in every step of the`
  line process;
  line
  line `(b) ensuring that the childs rights are protected throughout the process of apprehending the child,`
  line `inquiry, aftercare and rehabilitation;`
  line
  line `(c) ensuring availability of legal aid for the child through the legal services institutions;`
  line
  line `(d) wherever necessary the Board shall provide an interpreter or translator, having such`
  line `qualifications, experience, and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed, to the child if he fails to`
  line `understand the language used in the proceedings;`
  line
  line `(e) directing the Probation Officer, or in case a Probation Officer is not available to the Child`
  line `Welfare Officer or a social worker, to undertake a social investigation into the case and submit a`
  line `social investigation report within a period of fifteen days from the date of first production before the`
  line `Board to ascertain the circumstances in which the alleged offence was committed;`
  line
  line `(f) adjudicate and dispose of cases of children in conflict with law in accordance with the process`
  line `of inquiry specified in section 14;`
  line
  line `(g) transferring to the Committee, matters concerning the child alleged to be in conflict with law,`
  line `stated to be in need of care and protection at any stage, thereby recognising that a child in conflict`
  line `with law can also be a child in need of care simultaneously and there is a need for the Committee and`
  line `the Board to be both involved;`
  line
  line `(h) disposing of the matter and passing a final order that includes an individual care plan for the`
  line `childs rehabilitation, including follow up by the Probation Officer or the District Child Protection`
  line `Unit or a member of a non-governmental organisation, as may be required;`
  line
  line `(i) conducting inquiry for declaring fit persons regarding care of children in conflict with law;`
  line
  line `(j) conducting at least one inspection visit every month of residential facilities for children in`
  line `conflict with law and recommend action for improvement in quality of services to the District Child`
  line `Protection Unit and the State Government;`
  line
  line `(k) order the police for registration of first information report for offences committed against any`
  line `child in conflict with law, under this Act or any other law for the time being in force, on a complaint`
  line `made in this regard;`
  line
  line `(l) order the police for registration of first information report for offences committed against any`
  line `child in need of care and protection, under this Act or any other law for the time being in force, on a`
  line `written complaint by a Committee in this regard;`
  line
  line `(m) conducting regular inspection of jails meant for adults to check if any child is lodged in such jails and take immediate measures for transfer of ^1[that child to an observation home or place of safety, as the case may be]; and`
  line
  line `(n) any other function as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12729)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Procedure to be followed by a Magistrate who has not been empowered under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12729&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `When a Magistrate, not empowered to exercise the powers of the Board under this Act is of the opinion`
  line `that the person alleged to have committed the offence and brought before him is a child, he shall, without`
  line `any delay, record such opinion and forward the child immediately along with the record of such`
  line `proceedings to the Board having jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) In case a person alleged to have committed an offence claims before a court other than a Board,`
  line `that the person is a child or was a child on the date of commission of the offence, or if the court itself is of`
  line `the opinion that the person was a child on the date of commission of the offence, the said court shall make`
  line `an inquiry, take such evidence as may be necessary (but not an affidavit) to determine the age of such`
  line `person, and shall record a finding on the matter, stating the age of the person as nearly as may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that such a claim may be raised before any court and it shall be recognised at any stage,`
  line `even after final disposal of the case, and such a claim shall be determined in accordance with the`
  line `provisions contained in this Act and the rules made thereunder even if the person has ceased to be a child`
  line `on or before the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) If the court finds that a person has committed an offence and was a child on the date of`
  line `commission of such offence, it shall forward the child to the Board for passing appropriate orders and the`
  line `sentence, if any, passed by the court shall be deemed to have no effect.`
  line
  line `(4) In case a person under this section is required to be kept in protective custody, while the persons`
  line `claim of being a child is being inquired into, such person may be placed, in the intervening period in a`
  line `place of safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12730)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Apprehension of child alleged to be in conflict with law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12730&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as a child alleged to be`
  line `in conflict with law is apprehended by the police, such child shall be placed under the charge of the`
  line `special juvenile police unit or the designated child welfare police officer, who shall produce the child before the Board without any loss of time but within a period of twenty-four hours of apprehending the`
  line `child excluding the time necessary for the journey, from the place where such child was apprehended:`
  line
  line `Provided that in no case, a child alleged to be in conflict with law shall be placed in a police lockup or`
  line `lodged in a jail.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall make rules consistent with this Act,—`
  line
  line `(i) to provide for persons through whom (including registered voluntary or non-governmental`
  line `organisations) any child alleged to be in conflict with law may be produced before the Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) to provide for the manner in which the child alleged to be in conflict with law may be sent to`
  line `an observation home or place of safety, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12731)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Role of person in whose charge child in conflict with law is placed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12731&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any person in whose`
  line `charge a child in conflict with law is placed, shall while the order is in force, have responsibility of the`
  line `said child, as if the said person was the childs parent and responsible for the childs maintenance:`
  line
  line `Provided that the child shall continue in such persons charge for the period stated by the Board,`
  line `notwithstanding that the said child is claimed by the parents or any other person except when the Board is`
  line `of the opinion that the parent or any other person are fit to exercise charge over such child.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12732)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Bail to a person who is apparently a child alleged to be in conflict with law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12732&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any`
  line `person, who is apparently a child and is alleged to have committed a abailable or non-bailable offence, is`
  line `apprehended or detained by the police or appears or brought before a Board, such person shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, be released on bail with or without surety or placed under the supervision`
  line `of a probation officer or under the care of any fit person:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person shall not be so released if there appears reasonable grounds for believing`
  line `that the release is likely to bring that person into association with any known criminal or expose the said`
  line `person to moral, physical or psychological danger or the persons release would defeat the ends of justice,`
  line `and the Board shall record the reasons for denying the bail and circumstances that led to such a decision.`
  line
  line `(2) When such person having been apprehended is not released on bail under sub-section (1) by the officer-in-charge of the police station, such officer shall cause the person to be kept only in an observation home ^1[or a place of safety, as the case may be] in such manner as may be prescribed until the person can be brought before a Board.`
  line
  line `(3) When such person is not released on bail under sub-section (1) by the Board, it shall make an`
  line `order sending him to an observation home or a place of safety, as the case may be, for such period during`
  line `the pendency of the inquiry regarding the person, as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(4) When a child in conflict with law is unable to fulfil the conditions of bail order within seven days`
  line `of the bail order, such child shall be produced before the Board for modification of the conditions of bail.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12733)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Information to parents, guardian or probation officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12733&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a child alleged to be in`
  line `conflict with law is apprehended, the officer designated as Child Welfare Police Officer of the police`
  line `station, or the special juvenile police unit to which such child is brought, shall, as soon as possible after`
  line `apprehending the child, inform—`
  line
  line `(i) the parent or guardian of such child, if they can be found, and direct them to be present at the`
  line `Board before which the child is produced; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the probation officer, or if no probation officer is available, a Child Welfare Officer, for`
  line `preparation and submission within two weeks to the Board, a social investigation report containing`
  line `information regarding the antecedents and family background of the child and other material`
  line `circumstances likely to be of assistance to the Board for making the inquiry.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a child is released on bail, the probation officer or the Child Welfare Officer shall be`
  line `informed by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12734)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Inquiry by Board regarding child in conflict with law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12734&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a child alleged to be in`
  line `conflict with law is produced before Board, the Board shall hold an inquiry in accordance with the provisions of this Act and may pass such orders in relation to such child as it deems fit under sections 17`
  line `and 18 of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The inquiry under this section shall be completed within a period of four months from the date of`
  line `first production of the child before the Board, unless the period is extended, for a maximum period of two`
  line `more months by the Board, having regard to the circumstances of the case and after recording the reasons`
  line `in writing for such extension.`
  line
  line `(3) A preliminary assessment in case of heinous offences under section 15 shall be disposed of by the`
  line `Board within a period of three months from the date of first production of the child before the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) If inquiry by the Board under sub-section (2) for petty offences remains inconclusive even after`
  line `the extended period, the proceedings shall stand terminated:`
  line
  line `Provided that for serious or heinous offences, in case the Board requires further extension of time for`
  line `completion of inquiry, the same shall be granted by the Chief Judicial Magistrate or, as the case may be,`
  line `the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, for reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board shall take the following steps to ensure fair and speedy inquiry, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) at the time of initiating the inquiry, the Board shall satisfy itself that the child in conflict with`
  line `law has not been subjected to any ill-treatment by the police or by any other person, including a`
  line `lawyer or probation officer and take corrective steps in case of such ill-treatment;`
  line
  line `(b) in all cases under the Act, the proceedings shall be conducted in simple manner as possible`
  line `and care shall be taken to ensure that the child, against whom the proceedings have been instituted, is`
  line `given child-friendly atmosphere during the proceedings;`
  line
  line `(c) every child brought before the Board shall be given the opportunity of being heard and`
  line `participate in the inquiry;`
  line
  line `(d) cases of petty offences, shall be disposed of by the Board through summary proceedings, as`
  line `per the procedure prescribed under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(e) inquiry of serious offences shall be disposed of by the Board, by following the procedure, for`
  line `trial in summons cases under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(f) inquiry of heinous offences,—`
  line
  line `(i) for child below the age of sixteen years as on the date of commission of an offence shall`
  line `be disposed of by the Board under clause (e);`
  line
  line `(ii) for child above the age of sixteen years as on the date of commission of an offence shall`
  line `be dealt with in the manner prescribed under section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12735)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Preliminary assessment into heinous offences by Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12735&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of a heinous offence`
  line `alleged to have been committed by a child, who has completed or is above the age of sixteen years, the`
  line `Board shall conduct a preliminary assessment with regard to his mental and physical capacity to commit`
  line `such offence, ability to understand the consequences of the offence and the circumstances in which he`
  line `allegedly committed the offence, and may pass an order in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 18:`
  line
  line `Provided that for such an assessment, the Board may take the assistance of experienced psychologists`
  line `or psycho-social workers or other experts.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, it is clarified that preliminary assessment is not a trial,`
  line `but is to assess the capacity of such child to commit and understand the consequences of the alleged`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(2) Where the Board is satisfied on preliminary assessment that the matter should be disposed of by`
  line `the Board, then the Board shall follow the procedure, as far as may be, for trial in summons case under`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974):`
  line
  line `Provided that the order of the Board to dispose of the matter shall be appealable under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 101:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the assessment under this section shall be completed within the period specified`
  line `in section 14.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12736)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Review of pendency of inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 7, (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12736&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Judicial Magistrate or the Chief Metropolitan`
  line `Magistrate shall review the pendency of cases of the Board once in every three months, and shall direct`
  line `the Board to increase the frequency of its sittings or may recommend the constitution of additional`
  line Boards.
  line
  line `(2) The number of cases pending before the Board, duration of such pendency, nature of pendency`
  line `and reasons thereof shall be reviewed in every six months by a high level committee consisting of the`
  line `Executive Chairperson of the State Legal Services Authority, who shall be the Chairperson, the Home`
  line `Secretary, the Secretary responsible for the implementation of this Act in the State and a representative`
  line `from a voluntary or non-governmental organisation to be nominated by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3) The information of such pendency shall also be furnished by the Board to the Chief Judicial`
  line `Magistrate or the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate and the District Magistrate on quarterly basis in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) The District Magistrate may, as and when required, in the best interest of a child, call for any information from all the stakeholders including the Board and the Committee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12737)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Orders regarding a child not found to be in conflict with law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12737&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Board is satisfied`
  line `on inquiry that the child brought before it has not committed any offence, then notwithstanding anything`
  line `contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Board shall pass order to that effect.`
  line
  line `(2) In case it appears to the Board that the child referred to in sub-section (1) is in need of care and`
  line `protection, it may refer the child to the Committee with appropriate directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12738)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Orders regarding child found to be in conflict with law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 8, (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12738&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Board is satisfied on`
  line `inquiry that a child irrespective of age has committed a petty offence, or a serious offence, or a child`
  line `below the age of sixteen years has committed a heinous offence,`
  line `^1[or a child above the age of sixteen`
  line `years has committed a heinous offence and the Board has, after preliminary assessment under Section 15,`
  line `disposed of the matter] then, notwithstanding anything contrary contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, and based on the nature of offence, specific need for supervision or intervention,`
  line `circumstances as brought out in the social investigation report and past conduct of the child, the Board`
  line `may, if it so thinks fit,---`
  line
  line `(a) allow the child to go home after advice or admonition by following appropriate inquiry and`
  line `counselling to such child and to his parents or the guardian;`
  line
  line `(b) direct the child to participate in group counselling and similar activities;`
  line
  line `(c) order the child to perform community service under the supervision of an organisation or`
  line `institution, or a specified person, persons or group of persons identified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) order the child or parents or the guardian of the child to pay fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in case the child is working, it may be ensured that the provisions of any labour`
  line `law for the time being in force are not violated;`
  line
  line `(e) direct the child to be released on probation of good conduct and placed under the care of any`
  line `parent, guardian or fit person, on such parent, guardian or fit person executing a bond, with or without`
  line `surety, as the Board may require, for the good behaviour and child's well-being for any period not`
  line `exceeding three years;`
  line
  line `(f) direct the child to be released on probation of good conduct and placed under the care and`
  line `supervision of any fit facility for ensuring the good behaviour and child's well-being for any period`
  line `not exceeding three years;`
  line
  line `(g) direct the child to be sent to a special home, for such period, not exceeding three years, as it`
  line `thinks fit, for providing reformative services including education, skill development, counselling,`
  line `behaviour modification therapy, and psychiatric support during the period of stay in the special home:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the conduct and behaviour of the child has been such that, it would not be in the`
  line `child's interest, or in the interest of other children housed in a special home, the Board may send such`
  line `child to the place of safety.`
  line
  line `(2) If an order is passed under clauses (a) to (g) of sub-section (1), the Board may, in addition pass`
  line `orders to---`
  line
  line `(i) attend school; or`
  line
  line `(ii) attend a vocational training centre; or`
  line
  line `(iii) attend a therapeutic centre; or`
  line
  line `(iv) prohibit the child from visiting, frequenting or appearing at a specified place; or`
  line
  line `(v) undergo a de-addiction programme.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Board after preliminary assessment under section 15 pass an order that there is a need`
  line `for trial of the said child as an adult, then the Board may order transfer of the trial of the case to the`
  line `Children's Court having jurisdiction to try such offences.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12739)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Powers of Children’s Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12739&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the receipt of preliminary assessment from the Board`
  line `under section 15, the Children's Court may decide that---`
  line
  line `(i) there is a need for trial of the child as an adult as per the provisions of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and pass appropriate orders after trial subject to the provisions of this`
  line `section and section 21, considering the special needs of the child, the tenets of fair trial and`
  line `maintaining a child friendly atmosphere;`
  line
  line `(ii) there is no need for trial of the child as an adult and may conduct an inquiry as a Board and`
  line `pass appropriate orders in accordance with the provisions of section 18.`
  line
  line `(2) The Children's Court shall ensure that the final order, with regard to a child in conflict with law,`
  line `shall include an individual care plan for the rehabilitation of child, including follow up by the probation`
  line `officer or the District Child Protection Unit or a social worker.`
  line
  line `(3) The Children's Court shall ensure that the child who is found to be in conflict with law is sent to a`
  line `place of safety till he attains the age of twenty-one years and thereafter, the person shall be transferred to`
  line `a jail:`
  line
  line `Provided that the reformative services including educational services, skill development, alternative`
  line `therapy such as counselling, behaviour modification therapy, and psychiatric support shall be provided to`
  line `the child during the period of his stay in the place of safety.`
  line
  line `(4) The Children's Court shall ensure that there is a periodic follow up report every year by the`
  line `probation officer or the District Child Protection Unit or a social worker, as required, to evaluate the`
  line `progress of the child in the place of safety and to ensure that there is no ill-treatment to the child in any`
  line form.
  line
  line `(5) The reports under sub-section (4) shall be forwarded to the Children's Court for record and follow`
  line `up, as may be required.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12740)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Child attained age of twenty-one years and yet to complete prescribed term of stay in place of safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12740&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the child in conflict with the law attains the age of twenty-one years and is yet to`
  line `complete the term of stay, the Childrens Court shall provide for a follow up by the probation officer or`
  line `the District Child Protection Unit or a social worker or by itself, as required, to evaluate if such child has`
  line `undergone reformative changes and if the child can be a contributing member of the society and for this`
  line `purpose the progress records of the child under sub-section (4) of section 19, along with evaluation of`
  line `relevant experts are to be taken into consideration.`
  line
  line `(2) After the completion of the procedure specified under sub-section (1), the Children's Court may—`
  line
  line `(i) decide to release the child on such conditions as it deems fit which includes appointment of a`
  line `monitoring authority for the remainder of the prescribed term of stay;`
  line
  line `(ii) decide that the child shall complete the remainder of his term in a jail:`
  line
  line `Provided that each State Government shall maintain a list of monitoring authorities and monitoring`
  line `procedures as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12741)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Order that may not be passed against a child in conflict with law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12741&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No child in conflict with`
  line `law shall be sentenced to death or for life imprisonment without the possibility of release, for any such`
  line `offence, either under the provisions of this Act or under the provisions of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) or any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12742)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Proceeding under Chapter VIII of the Code of Criminal Procedure not to apply against child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12742&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), or any preventive detention law for the time being in force, no proceeding shall be instituted`
  line `and no order shall be passed against any child under Chapter VIII of the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12743)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `No joint proceedings of child in conflict with law and person not a child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12743&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 223 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)`
  line `or in any other law for the time being in force, there shall be no joint proceedings of a child alleged to be`
  line `in conflict with law, with a person who is not a child.`
  line
  line `(2) If during the inquiry by the Board or by the Childrens Court, the person alleged to be in conflict`
  line `with law is found that he is not a child, such person shall not be tried along with a child.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (12744)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Removal of disqualification on the findings of an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12744&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, a child who has committed an offence and has been`
  line `dealt with under the provisions of this Act shall not suffer disqualification, if any, attached to a conviction`
  line `of an offence under such law:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a child who has completed or is above the age of sixteen years and is found to`
  line `be in conflict with law by the Children's Court under clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 19, the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall make an order directing the Police, or by the Children's Court to its own registry`
  line `that the relevant records of such conviction shall be destroyed after the expiry of the period of appeal or,`
  line `as the case may be, a reasonable period as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a heinous offence where the child is found to be in conflict with law under`
  line `clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 19, the relevant records of conviction of such child shall be`
  line `retained by the Children's Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (12745)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Special provision in respect of pending cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12745&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,`
  line `all proceedings in respect of a child alleged or found to be in conflict with law pending before any Board`
  line `or court on the date of commencement of this Act, shall be continued in that Board or court as if this Act`
  line `had not been enacted.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (12746)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Provision with respect of run away child in conflict with law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12746&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `to the contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force, any police officer may take charge`
  line `of a child in conflict with law who has run away from a special home or an observation home or a place`
  line `of safety or from the care of a person or institution under whom the child was placed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The child referred to in sub-section (1) shall be produced, within twenty-four hours, preferably`
  line `before the Board which passed the original order in respect of that child, if possible, or to the nearest`
  line `Board where the child is found.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall ascertain the reasons for the child having run away and pass appropriate orders`
  line `for the child to be sent back either to the institution or person from whose custody the child had run away`
  line `or any other similar place or person, as the Board may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may also give additional directions regarding any special steps that may be`
  line `deemed necessary, for the best interest of the child.`
  line
  line `(4) No additional proceeding shall be instituted in respect of such child.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (12747)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Child Welfare Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12747&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette constitute for every district, one or more Child Welfare Committees for exercising the powers and`
  line `to discharge the duties conferred on such Committees in relation to children in need of care and protection`
  line `under this Act and ensure that induction training and sensitisation of all members of the committee is`
  line `provided within two months from the date of notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall consist of a Chairperson, and four other members as the State Government`
  line `may think fit to appoint, of whom at least one shall be a woman and another, an expert on the matters`
  line `concerning children.`
  line
  line `(3) The District Child Protection Unit shall provide a Secretary and other staff that may be required`
  line `for secretarial support to the Committee for its effective functioning.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) No person shall be appointed as a member of the Committee unless he has a degree in child psychology or psychiatry or law or social work or sociology or human health or education or human development or special education for differently abled children and has been actively involved in health,`
  line `education or welfare activities pertaining to children for seven years or is a practicing professional with a degree in child psychology or psychiatry or law or social work or sociology or human health or education or human development or special education for differently abled children.`
  line
  line `(4A) No person shall be eligible for selection as a member of the Committee, if he--`
  line
  line `(i) has any past record of violation of human rights or child rights,`
  line
  line `(ii) has been convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude, and such conviction has not been reversed or has not been granted full pardon in respect of such offence,`
  line
  line `(iii) has been removed or dismissed from service of the Government of India or State Government or an undertaking or corporation owned or controlled by the Government of India or State Government,`
  line
  line `(iv) has ever indulged in child abuse or employment of child labour or immoral act or any other violation of human rights or immoral acts, or`
  line
  line `(v) is part of management of a child care institution in a District.]`
  line
  line `(5) No person shall be appointed as a member unless he possesses such other qualifications as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) No person shall be appointed for a period of more than three years as a member of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(7) The appointment of any member of the Committee shall be terminated by the State Government after making an inquiry, if--`
  line
  line `(i) he has been found guilty of misuse of power vested on him under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) he has been convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude and such conviction has not been reversed or he has not been granted full pardon in respect of such offence;`
  line
  line `(iii) he fails to attend the proceedings of the Committee consecutively for three months without any valid reason or he fails to attend ^2[minimum] three-fourths of the sittings in a year.`
  line
  line `^3[(8) The Committee shall submit a report to the District Magistrate in such form as may be prescribed and the District Magistrate shall conduct a quarterly review of the functioning of the Committee.]`
  line
  line `(9) The Committee shall function as a Bench and shall have the powers conferred by the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) on a Metropolitan Magistrate or, as the case may be, a Judicial Magistrate of First Class.`
  line
  line `^4[(10) The District Magistrate shall be the grievance redressal authority to entertain any grievance arising out of the functioning of the Committee and the affected child or anyone connected with the child, as the case may be, may file a complaint before the District Magistrate who shall take cognizance of the action of the Committee and, after giving the parties an opportunity of being heard, pass appropriate order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 9, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 9, for "less than" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for sub-section (8) (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for sub-section (10) (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (12748)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Procedure in relation to Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12748&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee shall meet at least twenty days in a`
  line `month and shall observe such rules and procedures with regard to the transaction of business at its`
  line `meetings, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A visit to an existing child care institution by the Committee, to check its functioning and well`
  line `being of children shall be considered as a sitting of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) A child in need of care and protection may be produced before an individual member of the`
  line `Committee for being placed in a Childrens Home or fit person when the Committee is not in session.`
  line
  line `(4) In the event of any difference of opinion among the members of the Committee at the time of`
  line `taking any decision, the opinion of the majority shall prevail but where there is no such majority, the`
  line `opinion of the Chairperson shall prevail.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Committee may act, notwithstanding the absence`
  line `of any member of the Committee, and no order made by the Committee shall be invalid by reason only of`
  line `the absence of any member during any stage of the proceeding.`
  line
  line `Provided that there shall be at least three members present at the time of final disposal of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (12749)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Powers of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12749&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee shall have the authority to dispose of cases for the`
  line `care, protection, treatment, development and rehabilitation of children in need of care and protection, as`
  line `well as to provide for their basic needs and protection.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a Committee has been constituted for any area, such Committee shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, but save as otherwise expressly provided`
  line `in this Act, have the power to deal exclusively with all proceedings under this Act relating to children in`
  line `need of care and protection.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (12750)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Functions and responsibilities of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12750&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The functions and responsibilities of the`
  line `Committee shall include---`
  line
  line `(i) taking cognizance of and receiving the children produced before it;`
  line
  line `(ii) conducting inquiry on all issues relating to and affecting the safety and well-being of the`
  line `children under this Act;`
  line
  line `(iii) directing the Child Welfare Officers or probation officers or District Child Protection Unit or`
  line `non-governmental organisations to conduct social investigation and submit a report before the`
  line Committee;
  line
  line `(iv) conducting inquiry for declaring fit persons for care of children in need of care and`
  line protection;
  line
  line `(v) directing placement of a child in foster care;`
  line
  line `(vi) ensuring care, protection, appropriate rehabilitation or restoration of children in need of care`
  line `and protection, based on the child's individual care plan and passing necessary directions to parents`
  line `or guardians or fit persons or children's homes or fit facility in this regard;`
  line
  line `(vii) selecting registered institution for placement of each child requiring institutional support,`
  line `based on the child's age, gender, disability and needs and keeping in mind the available capacity of`
  line `the institution;`
  line
  line `(viii) conducting at least two inspection visits per month of residential facilities for children in`
  line `need of care and protection and recommending action for improvement in quality of services to the`
  line `District Child Protection Unit and the State Government;`
  line
  line `(ix) certifying the execution of the surrender deed by the parents and ensuring that they are given`
  line `time to reconsider their decision as well as making all efforts to keep the family together;`
  line
  line `(x) ensuring that all efforts are made for restoration of abandoned or lost children to their families`
  line `following due process, as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(xi) declaration of orphan, abandoned and surrendered child as legally free for adoption after due`
  line inquiry;
  line
  line `(xii) taking suo motu cognizance of cases and reaching out to children in need of care and`
  line `protection, who are not produced before the Committee, provided that such decision is taken by at`
  line `least three members;`
  line
  line `(xiii) taking action for rehabilitation of sexually abused children who are reported as children in`
  line `need of care and protection to the Committee by Special Juvenile Police Unit or local police, as the`
  line `case may be, under the Protection of Children from Sexual Offences Act, 2012 (32 of 2012);`
  line
  line `(xiv) dealing with cases referred by the Board under sub-section (2) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(xv) co-ordinate with the police, labour department and other agencies involved in the care and`
  line `protection of children with support of the District Child Protection Unit or the State Government;`
  line
  line `(xvi) in case of a complaint of abuse of a child in any child care institution, the Committee shall`
  line `conduct an inquiry and give directions to the police or the District Child Protection Unit or labour`
  line `department or childline services, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(xvii) accessing appropriate legal services for children;`
  line
  line `(xviii) such other functions and responsibilities, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (12751)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Production before Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12751&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any child in need of care and protection may be produced`
  line `before the Committee by any of the following persons, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) any police officer or special juvenile police unit or a designated Child Welfare Police Officer`
  line `or any officer of District Child Protection Unit or inspector appointed under any labour law for the`
  line `time being in force;`
  line
  line `(ii) any public servant;`
  line
  line `(iii) Childline Services or any voluntary or non-governmental organisation or any agency as may`
  line `be recognised by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(iv) Child Welfare Officer or probation officer;`
  line
  line `(v) any social worker or a public spirited citizen;`
  line
  line `(vi) by the child himself; or`
  line
  line `(vii) any nurse, doctor or management of a nursing home, hospital or maternity home:`
  line
  line `Provided that the child shall be produced before the Committee without any loss of time but within a`
  line `period of twenty-four hours excluding the time necessary for the journey.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may make rules consistent with this Act, to provide for the manner of`
  line `submitting the report to the Committee and the manner of sending and entrusting the child to childrens`
  line `home or fit facility or fit person, as the case may be, during the period of the inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (12752)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Mandatory reporting regarding a child found separated from guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 10, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12752&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any individual`
  line `or a police officer or any functionary of any organisation or a nursing home or hospital or maternity`
  line `home, who or which finds and takes charge, or is handed over a child who appears or claims to be`
  line `abandoned or lost, or a child who appears or claims to be an orphan without family support, shall within`
  line `twenty-four hours (excluding the time necessary for the journey), give information to the Childline`
  line `Services or the nearest police station or to a Child Welfare Committee or to the District Child Protection`
  line `Unit, or hand over the child to a child care institution registered under this Act, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The information regarding a child referred to in sub-section (1) shall be uploaded by the Committee or the District Child Protection Unit or the child care institution, as the case may be, on a portal as may be specified by the Central Government in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (12753)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Offence of non-reporting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12753&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `If information regarding a child as required under section 32 is not`
  line `given within the period specified in the said section, then, such act shall be regarded as an offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (12754)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Penalty for non-reporting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12754&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any person who has committed an offence under section 33 shall`
  line `be liable to imprisonment up to six months or fine of ten thousand rupees or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (12755)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Surrender of children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12755&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) A parent or guardian, who for physical, emotional and social factors`
  line `beyond their control, wishes to surrender a child, shall produce the child before the Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) If, after prescribed process of inquiry and counselling, the Committee is satisfied, a surrender deed`
  line `shall be executed by the parent or guardian, as the case may be, before the Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) The parents or guardian who surrendered the child, shall be given two months time to reconsider`
  line `their decision and in the intervening period the Committee shall either allow, after due inquiry, the child to be with the parents or guardian under supervision, or place the child in a Specialised Adoption Agency,`
  line `if he or she is below six years of age, or a childrens home if he is above six years.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (12756)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title Inquiry.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12756&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) On production of a child or receipt of a report under section 31, the Committee`
  line `shall hold an inquiry in such manner as may be prescribed and the Committee, on its own or on the report`
  line `from any person or agency as specified in sub-section (2) of section 31, may pass an order to send the`
  line `child to the childrens home or a fit facility or fit person, and for speedy social investigation by a social`
  line `worker or Child Welfare Officer or Child Welfare Police Officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that all children below six years of age, who are orphan, surrendered or appear to be`
  line `abandoned shall be placed in a Specialised Adoption Agency, where available.`
  line
  line `(2) The social investigation shall be completed within fifteen days so as to enable the Committee to`
  line `pass final order within four months of first production of the child:`
  line
  line `Provided that for orphan, abandoned or surrendered children, the time for completion of inquiry shall`
  line `be as specified in section 38.`
  line
  line `(3) After the completion of the inquiry, if Committee is of the opinion that the said child has no`
  line `family or ostensible support or is in continued need of care and protection, it may send the child to a`
  line `Specialised Adoption Agency if the child is below six years of age, childrens home or to a fit facility or`
  line `person or foster family, till suitable means of rehabilitation are found for the child, as may be prescribed,`
  line `or till the child attains the age of eighteen years:`
  line
  line `Provided that the situation of the child placed in a childrens home or with a fit facility or person or a`
  line `foster family, shall be reviewed by the Committee, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Committee shall submit a quarterly report on the nature of disposal of cases and pendency of`
  line `cases to the District Magistrate in the manner as may be prescribed, for review of pendency of cases.`
  line
  line `(5) After review under sub-section (4), the District Magistrate shall direct the Committee to take`
  line `necessary remedial measures to address the pendency, if necessary and send a report of such reviews to`
  line `the State Government, who may cause the constitution of additional Committees, if required:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the pendency of cases continues to be unaddressed by the Committee even after three`
  line `months of receiving such directions, the State Government shall terminate the said Committee and shall`
  line `constitute a new Committee.`
  line
  line `(6) In anticipation of termination of the Committee and in order that no time is lost in constituting a`
  line `new Committee, the State Government shall maintain a standing panel of eligible persons to be appointed`
  line `as members of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(7) In case of any delay in the constitution of a new Committee under sub-section (5), the Child`
  line `Welfare Committee of a nearby district shall assume responsibility in the intervening period.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (12757)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Orders passed regarding a child in need of care and protection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. The words "submitted by Child Welfare Officer" omitted by Act 23 of 2021, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12757&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee on being`
  line `satisfied through the inquiry that the child before the Committee is a child in need of care and protection,`
  line `may, on consideration of Social Investigation Report ^1[***] and taking into account the child's wishes in case the child is sufficiently mature to take a view, pass one or more of the following orders, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) declaration that a child is in need of care and protection;`
  line
  line `(b) restoration of the child to parents or guardian or family with or without supervision of Child`
  line `Welfare Officer or designated social worker;`
  line
  line `(c) placement of the child in Children's Home or fit facility or Specialised Adoption Agency for`
  line `the purpose of adoption for long term or temporary care, keeping in mind the capacity of the`
  line `institution for housing such children, either after reaching the conclusion that the family of the child`
  line `cannot be traced or even if traced, restoration of the child to the family is not in the best interest of the`
  line child;
  line
  line `(d) placement of the child with fit person for long term or temporary care;`
  line
  line `(e) foster care orders under section 44;`
  line
  line `(f) sponsorship orders under section 45;`
  line
  line `(g) directions to persons or institutions or facilities in whose care the child is placed, regarding`
  line `care, protection and rehabilitation of the child, including directions relating to immediate shelter and`
  line `services such as medical attention, psychiatric and psychological support including need-based`
  line `counselling, occupational therapy or behaviour modification therapy, skill training, legal aid,`
  line `educational services, and other developmental activities, as required, as well as follow-up and`
  line `coordination with the District Child Protection Unit or State Government and other agencies;`
  line
  line `(h) declaration that the child is legally free for adoption under section 38.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee may also pass orders for---`
  line
  line `(i) declaration of fit persons for foster care;`
  line
  line `(ii) getting after care support under section 46 of the Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any other order related to any other function as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (12758)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Procedure for declaring a child legally free for adoption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12758&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of orphan and`
  line `abandoned child, the Committee shall make all efforts for tracing the parents or guardians of the child and`
  line `on completion of such inquiry, if it is established that the child is either an orphan having no one to take`
  line `care, or abandoned, the Committee shall declare the child legally free for adoption:`
  line
  line `Provided that such declaration shall be made within a period of two months from the date of`
  line `production of the child, for children who are up to two years of age and within four months for children`
  line `above two years of age:`
  line
  line `Provided further that notwithstanding anything contained in this regard in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, no first information report shall be registered against any biological parent in the process`
  line `of inquiry relating to an abandoned or surrendered child under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In case of surrendered child, the institution where the child has been placed by the Committee on`
  line `an application for surrender, shall bring the case before the Committee immediately on completion of the`
  line `period specified in section 35, for declaring the child legally free for adoption.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, a child of a`
  line `mentally retarded parents or a unwanted child of victim of sexual assault, such child may be declared free`
  line `for adoption by the Committee, by following the procedure under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The decision to declare an orphan, abandoned or surrendered child as legally free for adoption`
  line `shall be taken by at least three members of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The Committee shall inform ^1[the District Magistrate] the State Agency and the Authority regarding the number of children declared as legally free for adoption and number of cases pending for decision in the manner as may be prescribed, every month.`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (12759)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Process of rehabilitation and social re-integration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12759&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The process of rehabilitation and`
  line `social integration of children under this Act shall be undertaken, based on the individual care plan of the`
  line `child, preferably through family based care such as by restoration to family or guardian with or without`
  line `supervision or sponsorship, or adoption or foster care:`
  line
  line `Provided that all efforts shall be made to keep siblings placed in institutional or non-institutional care,`
  line `together, unless it is in their best interest not to be kept together.`
  line
  line `(2) For children in conflict with law the process of rehabilitation and social integration shall be`
  line `undertaken in the observation homes, if the child is not released on bail or in special homes or place of`
  line `safety or fit facility or with a fit person, if placed there by the order of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The children in need of care and protection who are not placed in families for any reason may be`
  line `placed in an institution registered for such children under this Act or with a fit person or a fit facility, on a`
  line `temporary or long-term basis, and the process of rehabilitation and social integration shall be undertaken`
  line `wherever the child is so placed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Children in need of care and protection who are leaving institutional care or children in`
  line `conflict with law leaving special homes or place of safety on attaining eighteen years of age, may be`
  line `provided financial support as specified in section 46, to help them to re-integrate into the mainstream of`
  line `the society.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (12760)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Restoration of child in need of care and protection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 13, (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12760&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The restoration and protection of a`
  line `child shall be the prime objective of any Children's Home, Specialised Adoption Agency or open shelter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Children's Home, Specialised Adoption Agency or an open shelter, as the case may be, shall`
  line `take such steps as are considered necessary for the restoration and protection of a child deprived of his`
  line `family environment temporarily or permanently where such child is under their care and protection.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall have the powers to restore any child in need of care and protection to his`
  line `parents, guardian or fit person, as the case may be, after determining the suitability of the parents or`
  line `guardian or fit person to take care of the child, and give them suitable directions.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, restoration and protection of a child means`
  line `restoration to`
  line
  line `(a) parents;`
  line
  line `(b) adoptive parents;`
  line
  line `(c) foster parents;`
  line
  line `(d) guardian; or`
  line
  line `(e) fit person.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) The Committee shall submit a quarterly report regarding restored, dead and runaway children to the State Government and the District Magistrate in such form as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (12761)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Registration of child care institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12761&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, all institutions, whether run by a State Government or by voluntary or`
  line `non-governmental organisations, which are meant, either wholly or partially, for housing children in need`
  line `of care and protection or children in conflict with law, shall, be registered under this Act in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed, ^1[***] regardless of whether they are receiving grants from the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government or not:`
  line
  line `Provided that the institutions having valid registration under the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2000 (56 of 2000) on the date of commencement of this Act shall be deemed to have been registered under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) At the time of registration under this section, the State Government ^2[shall, after considering the recommendations of the District Magistrate, determine] and record the capacity and purpose of the institution and shall register the institution as a Children's Home or open shelter or Specialised Adoption Agency or observation home or special home or place of safety, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of application for registration under sub-section (1), from an existing or new institution`
  line `housing children in need of care and protection or children in conflict with law, the State Government`
  line `may grant provisional registration, within one month from the date of receipt of application, for a`
  line `maximum period of six months, in order to bring such institution under the purview of this Act, and shall`
  line `determine the capacity of the Home which shall be mentioned in the registration certificate:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the said institution does not fulfil the prescribed criteria for registration, within the`
  line `period specified in sub-section (1), the provisional registration shall stand cancelled and the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (5) shall apply.`
  line
  line `(4) If the State Government does not issue a provisional registration certificate within one month from`
  line `the date of application, the proof of receipt of application for registration shall be treated as provisional`
  line `registration to run an institution for a maximum period of six months.`
  line
  line `(5) If the application for registration is not disposed of within six months by any officer or officers of`
  line `any State Government, it shall be regarded as dereliction of duty on their part by their higher controlling`
  line `authority and appropriate departmental proceedings shall be initiated.`
  line
  line `(6) The period of registration of an institution shall be five years, and it shall be subject to renewal in`
  line `every five years.`
  line
  line `(7) The State Government may, after following the procedure as may be prescribed, cancel or`
  line `withhold registration, as the case may be, of such institutions which fail to provide rehabilitation and`
  line `reintegration services as specified in section 53 and till such time that the registration of an institution is`
  line `renewed or granted, the State Government shall manage the institution.`
  line
  line `(8) Any child care institution registered under this section shall be duty bound to admit children,`
  line `subject to the capacity of the institution, as directed by the Committee, whether they are receiving grants`
  line `from the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government or not.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the inspection`
  line `committee appointed under section 54, shall have the powers to inspect any institution housing children,`
  line `even if not registered under this Act to determine whether such institution is housing children in need of`
  line `care and protection.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words ",within a period of six months from the date of commencement of this Act," omitted by Act 23 of 2021, s. 14, (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs by s. 14, ibid., for "shall determine" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (12762)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Penalty for non-registration of child care institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12762&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Any person, or persons, in-charge of`
  line `an institution housing children in need of care and protection and children in conflict with law, who fails`
  line `to comply with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 41, shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `which may extend to one year or a fine of not less than one lakh rupees or both:`
  line
  line `Provided that every thirty days delay in applying for registration shall be considered as a separate`
  line offence.
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (12763)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Open shelter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12763&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may establish and maintain, by itself or through`
  line `voluntary or non-governmental organisations, as many open shelters as may be required, and such open`
  line `shelters shall be registered as such, in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The open shelters referred to in sub-section (1) shall function as a community based facility for`
  line `children in need of residential support, on short-term basis, with the objective of protecting them from`
  line `abuse or weaning them, or keeping them, away from a life on the streets.`
  line
  line `(3) The open shelters shall send every month information, in the manner as may be prescribed,`
  line `regarding children availing the services of the shelter, to the District Child Protection Unit and the`
  line Committee.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (12764)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Foster care.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12764&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The children in need of care and protection may be placed in foster care,`
  line `including group foster care for their care and protection through orders of the Committee, after following`
  line `the procedure as may be prescribed in this regard, in a family which does not include the child's`
  line `biological or adoptive parents or in an unrelated family recognised as suitable for the purpose by the State`
  line `Government, for a short or extended period of time.`
  line
  line `(2) The selection of the foster family shall be based on family's ability, intent, capacity and prior`
  line `experience of taking care of children.`
  line
  line `(3) All efforts shall be made to keep siblings together in foster families, unless it is in their best`
  line `interest not to be kept together.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government, after taking into account the number of children, shall provide monthly`
  line `funding for such foster care through District Child Protection Unit after following the procedure, as may`
  line `be prescribed, for inspection to ensure well being of the children.`
  line
  line `(5) In cases where children have been placed in foster care for the reason that their parents have been`
  line `found to be unfit or incapacitated by the Committee, the child's parents may visit the child in the foster family at regular intervals, unless the Committee feels that such visits are not in the best interest of the`
  line `child, for reasons to be recorded therefor; and eventually, the child may return to the parents homes once`
  line `the parent's are determined by the Committee to be fit to take care of the child.`
  line
  line `(6) The foster family shall be responsible for providing education, health and nutrition to the child`
  line `and shall ensure the overall well being of the child in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The State Government may make rules for the purpose of defining the procedure, criteria and the`
  line `manner in which foster care services shall be provided for children.`
  line
  line `(8) The inspection of foster families shall be conducted every month by the Committee in the form as`
  line `may be prescribed to check the well-being of the child and whenever a foster family is found lacking in`
  line `taking care of the child, the child shall be removed from that foster family and shifted to another foster`
  line `family as the Committee may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(9) No child regarded as adoptable by the Committee shall be given for long-term foster care.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (12765)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title Sponsorship.
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12765&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall make rules for the purpose of undertaking various`
  line `programmes of sponsorship of children, such as individual to individual sponsorship, group sponsorship`
  line `or community sponsorship.`
  line
  line `(2) The criteria for sponsorship shall include,—`
  line
  line `(i) where mother is a widow or divorced or abandoned by family;`
  line
  line `(ii) where children are orphan and are living with the extended family;`
  line
  line `(iii) where parents are victims of life threatening disease;`
  line
  line `(iv) where parents are incapacitated due to accident and unable to take care of children both`
  line `financially and physically.`
  line
  line `(3) The duration of sponsorship shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The sponsorship programme may provide supplementary support to families, to Children's Homes`
  line `and to special homes to meet medical, nutritional, educational and other needs of the children, with a view`
  line `to improving their quality of life.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (12766)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `After care of children leaving child care institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12766&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Any child leaving a child care institution`
  line `on completion of eighteen years of age may be provided with financial support in order to facilitate`
  line `childs re-integration into the mainstream of the society in the manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (12767)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Observation homes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12767&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall establish and maintain in every district or`
  line `a group of districts, either by itself, or through voluntary or non-governmental organisations, observation`
  line `homes, which shall be registered under section 41 of this Act, for temporary reception, care and`
  line `rehabilitation of any child alleged to be in conflict with law, during the pendency of any inquiry under`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the State Government is of the opinion that any registered institution other than a home`
  line `established or maintained under sub-section (1), is fit for the temporary reception of such child alleged to`
  line `be in conflict with law during the pendency of any inquiry under this Act, it may register such institution`
  line `as an observation home for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by rules made under this Act, provide for the management and`
  line `monitoring of observation homes, including the standards and various types of services to be provided by`
  line `them for rehabilitation and social integration of a child alleged to be in conflict with law and the`
  line `circumstances under which, and the manner in which, the registration of an observation home may be`
  line `granted or withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(4) Every child alleged to be in conflict with law who is not placed under the charge of parent or`
  line `guardian and is sent to an observation home shall be segregated according to the child's age and gender,`
  line `after giving due consideration to physical and mental status of the child and degree of the offence`
  line committed.
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (12768)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Special homes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12768&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may establish and maintain either by itself or through`
  line `voluntary or non-governmental organisations, special homes, which shall be registered as such, in the`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, in every district or a group of districts, as may be required for rehabilitation`
  line `of those children in conflict with law who are found to have committed an offence and who are placed`
  line `there by an order of the Juvenile Justice Board made under section 18.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by rules, provide for the management and monitoring of special`
  line `homes, including the standards and various types of services to be provided by them which are necessary`
  line `for social re-integration of a child, and the circumstances under which, and the manner in which, the`
  line `registration of a special home may be granted or withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(3) The rules made under sub-section (2) may also provide for the segregation and separation of`
  line `children found to be in conflict with law on the basis of age, gender, the nature of offence committed by`
  line `them and the child's mental and physical status.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (12769)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Place of safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12769&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall set up atleast one place of safety in a State`
  line `registered under section 41, so as to place a person above the age of eighteen years or child in conflict`
  line `with law, who is between the age of sixteen to eighteen years and is accused of or convicted for`
  line `committing a heinous offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Every place of safety shall have separate arrangement and facilities for stay of such children or`
  line `persons during the process of inquiry and children or persons convicted of committing an offence.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by rules, prescribe the types of places that can be designated as place`
  line `of safety under sub-section (1) and the facilities and services that may be provided therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (12770)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Children’s Home.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12770&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may establish and maintain, in every district or`
  line `group of districts, either by itself or through voluntary or non-governmental organisations, Children's`
  line `Homes, which shall be registered as such, for the placement of children in need of care and protection for`
  line `their care, treatment, education, training, development and rehabilitation.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall designate any Children's Home as a home fit for children with special`
  line `needs delivering specialised services, depending on requirement.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by rules, provide for the monitoring and management of Children's`
  line `Homes including the standards and the nature of services to be provided by them, based on individual`
  line `care plans for each child.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (12771)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Fit facility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12771&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board or the Committee shall recognise a facility being run by a`
  line `Governmental organisation or a voluntary or non-governmental organisation registered under any law for`
  line `the time being in force to be fit to temporarily take the responsibility of a child for a specific purpose after`
  line `due inquiry regarding the suitability of the facility and the organisation to take care of the child in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board or the Committee may withdraw the recognition under sub-section (1) for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (12772)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Fit person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12772&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board or the Committee shall, after due verification of credentials,`
  line `recognise any person fit to temporarily receive a child for care, protection and treatment of such child for`
  line `a specified period and in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board or Committee, as the case may be, may withdraw the recognition granted under subsection`
  line `(1) for reasons to be recorded in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (12773)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Rehabilitation and re-integration services in institutions registered under this Act and management thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12773&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The services that shall be provided, by the institutions registered under this`
  line `Act in the process of rehabilitation and re-integration of children, shall be in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, which may include---`
  line
  line `(i) basic requirements such as food, shelter, clothing and medical attention as per the prescribed`
  line standards;
  line
  line `(ii) equipment such as wheel-chairs, prosthetic devices, hearing aids, braille kits, or any other`
  line `suitable aids and appliances as required, for children with special needs;`
  line
  line `(iii) appropriate education, including supplementary education, special education, and appropriate`
  line `education for children with special needs:`
  line
  line `Provided that for children between the age of six to fourteen years, the provisions of the Right of`
  line `Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act, 2009 (35 of 2009) shall apply;`
  line
  line `(iv) skill development;`
  line
  line `(v) occupational therapy and life skill education;`
  line
  line `(vi) mental health interventions, including counselling specific to the need of the child;`
  line
  line `(vii) recreational activities including sports and cultural activities;`
  line
  line `(viii) legal aid where required;`
  line
  line `(ix) referral services for education, vocational training, de-addiction, treatment of diseases where`
  line required;
  line
  line `(x) case management including preparation and follow up of individual care plan;`
  line
  line `(xi) birth registration;`
  line
  line `(xii) assistance for obtaining the proof of identity, where required; and`
  line
  line `(xiii) any other service that may reasonably be provided in order to ensure the well-being of the`
  line `child, either directly by the State Government, registered or fit individuals or institutions or through`
  line `referral services.`
  line
  line `(2) Every institution shall have a Management Committee, to be set up in a manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, to manage the institution and monitor the progress of every child.`
  line
  line `(3) The officer in-charge of every institution, housing children above six years of age, shall facilitate`
  line `setting up of children's committees for participating in such activities as may be prescribed, for the safety`
  line `and well-being of children in the institution.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (12774)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Inspection of institutions registered under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12774&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall appoint`
  line `inspection committees for the State and district, as the case may be, for all institutions registered or`
  line `recognised to be fit under this Act for such period and for such purposes, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Such inspection committees shall mandatorily conduct visits to all facilities housing children in the area allocated, at least once in three months in a team of not less than three members, of whom at least one shall be a woman and one shall be a medical officer, and submit reports of the findings of such visits within a week of their visit, to the ^1[District Magistrate], for further action.`
  line
  line `(3) On the submission of the report by the inspection committee within a week of the inspection, appropriate action shall be taken within a month by the ^2[District Magistrate] and a compliance report shall be submitted to the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 15, for "District Child Protection Units or State Government, as the case may be" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "District Child Protection Unit or the State Government" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (12775)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Evaluation of functioning of structures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 16, (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12775&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government or State Government ^1[or District Magistrate] may independently evaluate the functioning of the Board, Committee, special juvenile police units, registered institutions, or recognised fit facilities and persons, at such period and through such persons or institutions as may be prescribed by that Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In case such independent evaluation is conducted by both the Governments, the evaluation made`
  line `by the Central Government shall prevail.`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (12776)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title Adoption.
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 17, for "Court" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12776&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) Adoption shall be resorted to for ensuring right to family for the orphan,`
  line `abandoned and surrendered children, as per the provisions of this Act, the rules made thereunder and the`
  line `adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Adoption of a child from a relative by another relative, irrespective of their religion, can be made`
  line `as per the provisions of this Act and the adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this Act shall apply to the adoption of children made under the provisions of the Hindu`
  line `Adoption and Maintenance Act, 1956 (78 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(4) All inter-country adoptions shall be done only as per the provisions of this Act and the adoption`
  line `regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person, who takes or sends a child to a foreign country or takes part in any arrangement for transferring the care and custody of a child to another person in a foreign country without a valid order from the ^1[District Magistrate], shall be punishable as per the provisions of section 80.`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (12777)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Eligibility of prospective adoptive parents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12777&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The prospective adoptive parents shall be`
  line `physically fit, financially sound, mentally alert and highly motivated to adopt a child for providing a good`
  line `upbringing to him.`
  line
  line `(2) In case of a couple, the consent of both the spouses for the adoption shall be required.`
  line
  line `(3) A single or divorced person can also adopt, subject to fulfilment of the criteria and in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) A single male is not eligible to adopt a girl child.`
  line
  line `(5) Any other criteria that may be specified in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (12778)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Procedure for adoption by Indian prospective adoptive parents living in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12778&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Indian`
  line `prospective adoptive parents living in India, irrespective of their religion, if interested to adopt an orphan`
  line `or abandoned or surrendered child, may apply for the same to a Specialised Adoption Agency, in the`
  line `manner as provided in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The Specialised Adoption Agency shall prepare the home study report of the prospective adoptive`
  line `parents and upon finding them eligible, will refer a child declared legally free for adoption to them along`
  line `with the child study report and medical report of the child, in the manner as provided in the adoption`
  line `regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) On the receipt of the acceptance of the child from the prospective adoptive parents along with the child study report and medical report of the child signed by such parents, the Specialised Adoption Agency shall give the child in pre-adoption foster care and file an application ^1[before the District Magisrate] for obtaining the adoption order, in the manner as provided in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) On the receipt of a certified copy of the ^2[order passed by the District Magistrate], the Specialised Adoption Agency shall send immediately the same to the prospective adoptive parents.`
  line
  line `(5) The progress and wellbeing of the child in the adoptive family shall be followed up and`
  line `ascertained in the manner as provided in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "in the court" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "court order" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (12779)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Procedure for inter-country adoption of an orphan or abandoned or surrendered child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12779&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `If an orphan or abandoned or surrendered child could not be placed with an Indian or non-resident Indian`
  line `prospective adoptive parent despite the joint effort of the Specialised Adoption Agency and State Agency`
  line `within sixty days from the date the child has been declared legally free for adoption, such child shall be`
  line `free for inter-country adoption:`
  line
  line `Provided that children with physical and mental disability, siblings and children above five years of`
  line `age may be given preference over other children for such inter-country adoption, in accordance with the`
  line `adoption regulations, as may be framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) An eligible non-resident Indian or overseas citizen of India or persons of Indian origin shall be`
  line `given priority in inter-country adoption of Indian children.`
  line
  line `(3) A non-resident Indian or overseas citizen of India, or person of Indian origin or a foreigner, who`
  line `are prospective adoptive parents living abroad, irrespective of their religion, if interested to adopt an`
  line `orphan or abandoned or surrendered child from India, may apply for the same to an authorised foreign`
  line `adoption agency, or Central Authority or a concerned Government department in their country of habitual`
  line `residence, as the case may be, in the manner as provided in the adoption regulations framed by the`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(4) The authorised foreign adoption agency, or Central Authority, or a concerned Government`
  line `department, as the case may be, shall prepare the home study report of such prospective adoptive parents`
  line `and upon finding them eligible, will sponsor their application to Authority for adoption of a child from`
  line `India, in the manner as provided in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) On the receipt of the application of such prospective adoptive parents, the Authority shall`
  line `examine and if it finds the applicants suitable, then, it will refer the application to one of the Specialised`
  line `Adoption Agencies, where children legally free for adoption are available.`
  line
  line `(6) The Specialised Adoption Agency will match a child with such prospective adoptive parents and`
  line `send the child study report and medical report of the child to such parents, who in turn may accept the`
  line `child and return the child study and medical report duly signed by them to the said agency.`
  line
  line `(7) On receipt of the acceptance of the child from the prospective adoptive parents, the Specialised Adoption Agency shall file an application ^1[before the District Magistrate] for obtaining the adoption order, in the manner as provided in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(8) On the receipt of a certified copy of the ^2[order passed by the District Magistrate], the specialised adoption agency shall send immediately the same to Authority, State Agency and to the prospective adoptive parents, and obtain a passport for the child.`
  line
  line `(9) The Authority shall intimate about the adoption to the immigration authorities of India and the`
  line `receiving country of the child.`
  line
  line `(10) The prospective adoptive parents shall receive the child in person from the specialised adoption`
  line `agency as soon as the passport and visa are issued to the child.`
  line
  line `(11) The authorised foreign adoption agency, or Central Authority, or the concerned Government`
  line `department, as the case may be, shall ensure the submission of progress reports about the child in the`
  line `adoptive family and will be responsible for making alternative arrangement in the case of any disruption,`
  line `in consultation with Authority and concerned Indian diplomatic mission, in the manner as provided in the`
  line `adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(12) A foreigner or a person of Indian origin or an overseas citizen of India, who has habitual`
  line `residence in India, if interested to adopt a child from India, may apply to Authority for the same along`
  line `with a no objection certificate from the diplomatic mission of his country in India, for further necessary`
  line `actions as provided in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 19, for "in the court" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "court order" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (12780)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Procedure for inter-country relative adoption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 20, for "court" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12780&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) A relative living abroad, who intends to adopt a child from his relative in India shall obtain an order from the ^1[District Magistrate] and apply for no objection certificate from Authority, in the manner as provided in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall on receipt of the order under sub-section (1) and the application from either`
  line `the biological parents or from the adoptive parents, issue no objection certificate under intimation to the`
  line `immigration authority of India and of the receiving country of the child.`
  line
  line `(3) The adoptive parents shall, after receiving no objection certificate under sub-section (2), receive`
  line `the child from the biological parents and shall facilitate the contact of the adopted child with his siblings`
  line `and biological parents from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (12781)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Procedure for disposal of adoption proceedings`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12781&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `^1[Procedure for disposal of adoption proceedings].--- (1) Before issuing an adoption order, the ^2[District Magistrate] shall satisfy itself that---`
  line
  line `(a) the adoption is for the welfare of the child; (b) due consideration is given to the wishes of the`
  line `child having regard to the age and understanding of the child; and (c) that neither the prospective adoptive parents has given or agreed to give nor the specialised adoption agency or the parent or`
  line `guardian of the child in case of relative adoption has received or agreed to receive any payment or`
  line `reward in consideration of the adoption, except as permitted under the adoption regulations framed by`
  line `the Authority towards the adoption fees or service charge or child care corpus.`
  line
  line `(2) The adoption proceedings shall be held in camera and the case shall be disposed of by the ^3[District Magistrate] within a period of two months from the date of filing.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 21, for the marginal heading (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "court" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "court" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (12782)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Additional procedural requirements and documentation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12782&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) The documentation and other`
  line `procedural requirements, not expressly provided in this Act with regard to the adoption of an orphan,`
  line `abandoned and surrendered child by Indian prospective adoptive parents living in India, or by`
  line `non-resident Indian or overseas citizen of India or person of Indian origin or foreigner prospective`
  line `adoptive parents, shall be as per the adoption regulations framed by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The specialised adoption agency shall ensure that the adoption case of prospective adoptive`
  line `parents is disposed of within four months from the date of receipt of application and the authorised`
  line `foreign adoption agency, Authority and State Agency shall track the progress of the adoption case and`
  line `intervene wherever necessary, so as to ensure that the time line is adhered to.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (12783)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Effect of adoption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 22, for "court" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12783&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `A child in respect of whom an adoption order is issued by the ^1[District Magistrate], shall become the child of the adoptive parents, and the adoptive parents shall become the parents of the child as if the child had been born to the adoptive parents, for all purposes, including intestacy, with effect from the date on which the adoption order takes effect, and on and from such date all the ties of the child in the family of his or her birth shall stand severed and replaced by those created by the adoption order in the adoptive family:`
  line
  line `Provided that any property which has vested in the adopted child immediately before the date on`
  line `which the adoption order takes effect shall continue to vest in the adopted child subject to the obligations,`
  line `if any, attached to the ownership of such property including the obligations, if any, to maintain the`
  line `relatives in the biological family.`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (12784)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Reporting of adoption.`
  content `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, information regarding all adoption orders issued by the ^1[District Magistrate], shall be forwarded to Authority on monthly basis in the manner as provided in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority, so as to enable Authority to maintain the data on adoption.`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 23, for "concerned courts" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12784&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (12785)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Specialised Adoption Agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 24, for "court" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12785&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall recognise one or more`
  line `institutions or organisations in each district as a Specialised Adoption Agency, in such manner as may be`
  line `provided in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority, for the rehabilitation of orphan, abandoned`
  line `or surrendered children, through adoption and non-institutional care.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Agency shall furnish the name, address and contact details of the Specialised Adoption`
  line `Agencies along with copies of certificate or letter of recognition or renewal to Authority, as soon as the`
  line `recognition or renewal is granted to such agencies.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall get every Specialised Adoption Agency inspected at least once in a`
  line `year and take necessary remedial measures, if required.`
  line
  line `(4) In case any Specialised Adoption Agency is in default in taking necessary steps on its part as provided in this Act or in the adoption regulations framed by the Authority, for getting an orphan or abandoned or surrendered child legally free for adoption from the Committee or in completing the home study report of the prospective adoptive parents or in obtaining adoption order from the ^1[District Magistrate] within the stipulated time, such Specialised Adoption Agency shall be punishable with a fine which may extend up to fifty thousand rupees and in case of repeated default, the recognition of the Specialised Adoption Agency shall be withdrawn by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (12786)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Adoption of children residing in institutions not registered as adoption agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12786&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) All the`
  line `institutions registered under this Act, which may not have been recognised as Specialised Adoption`
  line `Agencies, shall also ensure that all orphan or abandoned or surrendered children under their care are reported, produced and declared legally free for adoption, by the Committee as per the provisions of`
  line `section 38.`
  line
  line `(2) All institutions referred to in sub-section (1) shall develop formal linkages with nearby`
  line `Specialised Adoption Agency and shall furnish details of the children declared legally free for adoption to`
  line `that Specialised Adoption Agency along with all relevant records in the manner as may be prescribed, for`
  line `the placement of such children in adoption.`
  line
  line `(3) If any such institution contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), it shall be`
  line `liable to fine of fifty thousand rupees for each instance to be imposed by the registering authority and it`
  line `may also attract de-recognition in the event of persistent flouting of such provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (12787)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `State Adoption Resource Agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12787&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall set up a State Adoption`
  line `Resource Agency for dealing with adoptions and related matters in the State under the guidance of`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(2) The State Agency, wherever already exists, shall be deemed to be set up under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (12788)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Central Adoption Resource Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12788&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `The Central Adoption Resource Agency existing`
  line `before the commencement of this Act, shall be deemed to have been constituted as the Central Adoption`
  line `Resource Authority under this Act to perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to promote in-country adoptions and to facilitate inter-State adoptions in co-ordination with`
  line `State Agency;`
  line
  line `(b) to regulate inter-country adoptions;`
  line
  line `(c) to frame regulations on adoption and related matters from time to time as may be necessary;`
  line
  line `(d) to carry out the functions of the Central Authority under the Hague Convention on Protection`
  line `of Children and Cooperation in respect of Inter-country Adoption;`
  line
  line `(e) any other function as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (12789)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Steering Committee of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 2018, s. 3 and the second Schedule, for "mentioned at (d) to (f)" (w.e.f. 5-1-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12789&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall have a Steering Committee with`
  line `following members:`
  line
  line `(a) Secretary, Ministry of Women and Child Development, Government of India, who shall be`
  line `the Chairperson--ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) Joint Secretary, Ministry of Women and Child Development, Government of India, dealing`
  line `with Authority--ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Joint Secretary, Ministry of Women and Child Development, Government of India, dealing`
  line `with Finance--ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) one State Adoption Resource Agency and two Specialised Adoption Agencies;`
  line
  line `(e) one adoptive parent and one adoptee;`
  line
  line `(f) one advocate or a professor having at least ten years of experience in family law;`
  line
  line `(g) Member-Secretary, who shall also be Chief Executive Officer of the organisation.`
  line
  line `(2) Criteria for the selection or nomination of the Members ^1[mentioned at clauses (d) to (f) of subsection (1)], their tenure as well as the terms and conditions of their appointment shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The Steering Committee shall have the following functions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) to oversee the functioning of Authority and review its working from time to time so that it`
  line `operates in most effective manner;`
  line
  line `(b) to approve the annual budget, annual accounts and audit reports as well as the action plan and`
  line `annual report of Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) to adopt the recruitment rules, service rules, financial rules of Authority as well as the other`
  line `regulations for the exercise of the administrative and programmatic powers within the organisation,`
  line `with the prior approval of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) any other function that may be vested with it by the Central Government from time to time.`
  line
  line `(4) The Steering Committee shall meet once in a month in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Authority shall function from its headquarter and through its regional offices as may be set up`
  line `as per its functional necessity.`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (12790)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Powers of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12790&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the efficient performance of its functions, Authority shall have`
  line `the following powers, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to issue instructions to any Specialised Adoption Agency or a Children Home or any child`
  line `care institution housing any orphan, abandoned or surrendered child, any State Agency or any`
  line `authorised foreign adoption agency and such directions shall be complied by such agencies;`
  line
  line `(b) recommending to the concerned Government or Authority to take appropriate action against`
  line `any official or functionary or institution under its administrative control, in case of persistent noncompliance`
  line `of the instructions issued by it;`
  line
  line `(c) forwarding any case of persistent non-compliance of its instructions by any official or`
  line `functionary or institution to a Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the same and the Magistrate to`
  line `whom any such case is forwarded shall proceed to hear the same as if the case has been forwarded to`
  line `him under section 346 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(d) any other power that may be vested with it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In case of any difference of opinion in an adoption case, including the eligibility of prospective`
  line `adoptive parents or of a child to be adopted, the decision of Authority shall prevail.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (12791)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Annual Report of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12791&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall submit an annual report to the Central`
  line `Government in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall cause the annual report of Authority to be laid before each House`
  line `of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (12792)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12792&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Authority by way of grants such sums of money as`
  line `the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for performing the functions of Authority under`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may spend such sums of money as it thinks fit for performing the functions, as`
  line `prescribed under this Act, and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the grants referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (12793)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Accounts and audit of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12793&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General at such`
  line `intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit shall be`
  line `payable by the Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Authority under this Act shall, have the same rights and privileges and the`
  line `Authority in connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to`
  line `demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to`
  line `inspect any of the offices of Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General or any other`
  line `person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded annually`
  line `to the Central Government by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall cause the audit report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (12794)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Prohibition on disclosure of identity of children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 25, for "in cases where the case" (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12794&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) No report in any newspaper, magazine,`
  line `news-sheet or audio-visual media or other forms of communication regarding any inquiry or investigation`
  line `or judicial procedure, shall disclose the name, address or school or any other particular, which may lead to`
  line `the identification of a child in conflict with law or a child in need of care and protection or a child victim`
  line `or witness of a crime, involved in such matter, under any other law for the time being in force, nor shall`
  line `the picture of any such child be published:`
  line
  line `Provided that for reasons to be recorded in writing, the Board or Committee, as the case may be,`
  line `holding the inquiry may permit such disclosure, if in its opinion such disclosure is in the best interest of`
  line `the child.`
  line
  line `(2) The Police shall not disclose any record of the child for the purpose of character certificate or otherwise ^1[in the pending case or in the case which] has been closed or disposed of.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person contravening the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to six months or fine which may extend to two lakh rupees or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (12795)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Punishment for cruelty to child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12795&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, having the actual charge of, or control over, a`
  line `child, assaults, abandons, abuses, exposes or wilfully neglects the child or causes or procures the child to`
  line `be assaulted, abandoned, abused, exposed or neglected in a manner likely to cause such child unnecessary`
  line `mental or physical suffering, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years or with fine of one lakh rupees or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case it is found that such abandonment of the child by the biological parents is due to`
  line `circumstances beyond their control, it shall be presumed that such abandonment is not wilful and the`
  line `penal provisions of this section shall not apply in such cases:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if such offence is committed by any person employed by or managing an`
  line `organisation, which is entrusted with the care and protection of the child, he shall be punished with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment which may extend up to five years, and fine which may extend up to five lakhs`
  line `rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided also that on account of the aforesaid cruelty, if the child is physically incapacitated or`
  line `develops a mental illness or is rendered mentally unfit to perform regular tasks or has risk to life or limb,`
  line `such person shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment, not less than three years but which may be`
  line `extended up to ten years and shall also be liable to fine of five lakhs rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (12796)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Employment of child for begging.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12796&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever employs or uses any child for the purpose of`
  line `begging or causes any child to beg shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `five years and shall also be liable to fine of one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if for the purpose of begging, the person amputates or maims the child, he shall be`
  line `punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term not less than seven years which may extend up to ten`
  line `years, and shall also be liable to fine of five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, having the actual charge of, or control over the child, abets the commission of an`
  line `offence under sub-section (1), shall be punishable with the same punishment as provided for in subsection`
  line `(1) and such person shall be considered to be unfit under sub-clause (v) of clause (14) of`
  line `section 2:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said child, shall not be considered a child in conflict with law under any`
  line `circumstances, and shall be removed from the charge or control of such guardian or custodian and`
  line `produced before the Committee for appropriate rehabilitation.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (12797)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Penalty for giving intoxicating liquor or narcotic drug or psychotropic substance to a child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12797&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Whoever gives, or causes to be given, to any child any intoxicating liquor or any narcotic drug or tobacco products or psychotropic substance, except on the order of a duly qualified medical practitioner,`
  line `shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and shall also`
  line `be liable to a fine which may extend up to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (12798)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Using a child for vending, peddling, carrying, supplying or smuggling any intoxicating liquor, narcotic drug or psychotropic substance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12798&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Whoever uses a child, for vending, peddling,`
  line `carrying, supplying or smuggling any intoxicating liquor, narcotic drug or psychotropic substance, shall`
  line `be liable for rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and shall also be liable to`
  line `a fine up to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (12799)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Exploitation of a child employee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12799&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time`
  line `being in force, whoever ostensibly engages a child and keeps him in bondage for the purpose of`
  line `employment or withholds his earnings or uses such earning for his own purposes shall be punishable with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years and shall also be liable to fine of one`
  line `lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the term "employment" shall also include selling`
  line `goods and services, and entertainment in public places for economic gain.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (12800)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Punitive measures for adoption without following prescribed procedures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12800&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `If any person or`
  line `organisation offers or gives or receives, any orphan, abandoned or surrendered child, for the purpose of`
  line `adoption without following the provisions or procedures as provided in this Act, such person or`
  line `organisation shall be punishable with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend`
  line `upto three years, or with fine of one lakh rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided in case where the offence is committed by a recognised adoption agency, in addition to the`
  line `above punishment awarded to the persons in-charge of, and responsible for the conduct of the day-to-day`
  line `affairs of the adoption agency, the registration of such agency under section 41 and its recognition under`
  line `section 65 shall also be withdrawn for a minimum period of one year.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (12801)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Sale and procurement of children for any purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12801&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Any person who sells or buys a child for`
  line `any purpose shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine of one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such offence is committed by a person having actual charge of the child,`
  line `including employees of a hospital or nursing home or maternity home, the term of imprisonment shall not`
  line `be less than three years and may extend up to seven years.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (12802)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Corporal punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12802&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person in-charge of or employed in a child care institution, who`
  line `subjects a child to corporal punishment with the aim of disciplining the child, shall be liable, on the first`
  line `conviction, to a fine of ten thousand rupees and for every subsequent offence, shall be liable for`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to three months or fine or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person employed in an institution referred to in sub-section (1), is convicted of an offence`
  line `under that sub-section, such person shall also be liable for dismissal from service, and shall also be`
  line `debarred from working directly with children thereafter.`
  line
  line `(3) In case, where any corporal punishment is reported in an institution referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `and the management of such institution does not cooperate with any inquiry or comply with the orders of`
  line `the Committee or the Board or court or State Government, the person in-charge of the management of the`
  line `institution shall be liable for punishment with imprisonment for a term not less than three years and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (12803)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Use of child by militant groups or other adults.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12803&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any non-State, self-styled militant group`
  line `or outfit declared as such by the Central Government, if recruits or uses any child for any purpose, shall`
  line `be liable for rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and shall also be liable to`
  line `fine of five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Any adult or an adult group uses children for illegal activities either individually or as a gang shall`
  line `be liable for rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and shall also be liable to`
  line `fine of five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (12804)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Kidnapping and abduction of child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12804&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act, the provisions of sections`
  line `359 to 369 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), shall mutatis mutandis apply to a child or a minor who`
  line `is under the age of eighteen years and all the provisions shall be construed accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (12805)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Offences committed on disabled children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12805&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits any of the offences referred to in`
  line `this Chapter on any child who is disabled as so certified by a medical practitioner, then, such person shall`
  line `be liable to twice the penalty provided for such offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this Act, the term "disability" shall have the same meaning as`
  line `assigned to it under clause (i) of section 2 of the Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities,`
  line `Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (12806)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Classification of offences and designated court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 26, for Section 86 (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12806&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `^1[86 Classification of offences and designated court.-- (1) Where an offence under this Act is punishable with imprisonment for a term of more than seven years, then, such offence shall be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence under this Act is punishable with imprisonment for a term of three years and above, but not more than seven years, then, such offence shall be non-cognizable and non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an offence, under this Act is punishable with imprisonment for less than three years or with fine only, then, such offence shall be non-cognizable and bailable.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or the Commission for Protection of Child Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006) or the Protection of Children from Sexual Offences Act, 2012 (32 of 2012), offences under this Act shall be triable by the Children's Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (12807)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title Abetment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes `1. Explanation subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 27, (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12807&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets any offence under this Act, if the act abetted is committed in`
  line `consequence of the abetment, shall be punished with the punishment provided for that offence.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "abetment" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in Section 107 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (12808)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Alternative punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12808&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `Where an act or omission constitutes an offence punishable under this`
  line `Act and also under any other law for the time being in force, then, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any such law, the offender found guilty of such offence shall be liable for punishment under such law`
  line `which provides for punishment which is greater in degree.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (12809)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Offence committed by child under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12809&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `Any child who commits any offence under`
  line `this Chapter shall be considered as a child in conflict with law under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (12810)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Attendance of parent or guardian of child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12810&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `The Committee or the Board, as the case may be,`
  line `before which a child is brought under any of the provisions of this Act, may, whenever it so thinks fit,`
  line `require any parent or guardian having the actual charge of the child to be present at any proceeding in`
  line `respect of that child.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (12811)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Dispensing with attendance of child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12811&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at any stage during the course of an inquiry, the`
  line `Committee or the Board is satisfied that the attendance of the child is not essential for the purpose of`
  line `inquiry, the Committee or the Board, as the case may be, shall dispense with the attendance of a child and`
  line `limit the same for the purpose of recording the statement and subsequently, the inquiry shall continue`
  line `even in the absence of the child concerned, unless ordered otherwise by the Committee or the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the attendance of a child is required before the Board or the Committee, such child shall be`
  line `entitled to travel reimbursement for self and one escort accompanying the child as per actual expenditure`
  line `incurred, by the Board, or the Committee or the District Child Protection Unit, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (12812)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Placement of a child suffering from disease requiring prolonged medical treatment in an approved place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12812&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `When a child, who has been brought before the Committee or the Board, is found to`
  line `be suffering from a disease requiring prolonged medical treatment or physical or mental complaint that`
  line `will respond to treatment, the Committee or the Board, as the case may be, may send the child to any`
  line `place recognised as a fit facility as prescribed for such period as it may think necessary for the required`
  line treatment.
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (12813)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Transfer of a child who is mentally ill or addicted to alcohol or other drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12813&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it`
  line `appears to the Committee or the Board that any child kept in a special home or an observation home or a`
  line `Childrens Home or in an institution in pursuance of the provisions of this Act, is a mentally ill person or`
  line `addicted to alcohol or other drugs which lead to behavioural changes in a person, the Committee or the`
  line `Board, may order removal of such child to a psychiatric hospital or psychiatric nursing home in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987) or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) In case the child had been removed to a psychiatric hospital or psychiatric nursing home under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Committee or the Board may, on the basis of the advice given in the certificate of`
  line `discharge of the psychiatric hospital or psychiatric nursing home, order to remove such child to an`
  line `Integrated Rehabilitation Centre for Addicts or similar centres maintained by the State Government for`
  line `mentally ill persons (including the persons addicted to any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance) and`
  line `such removal shall be only for the period required for the inpatient treatment of such child.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Integrated Rehabilitation Centre for Addicts" shall have the meaning assigned to it under the`
  line `scheme called Central Sector Scheme of Assistance for Prevention of Alcoholism and Substance`
  line `(Drugs) Abuse and for Social Defence Services framed by the Central Government in the Ministry`
  line `of Social Justice and Empowerment or any other corresponding scheme for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) "mentally ill person" shall have the same meaning assigned to it in clause (l) of section 2 of`
  line `the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987);`
  line
  line `(c) "psychiatric hospital" or "psychiatric nursing home" shall have the same meaning assigned to`
  line `it in clause (q) of section 2 of the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (12814)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Presumption and determination of age.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12814&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, it is obvious to the Committee or the`
  line `Board, based on the appearance of the person brought before it under any of the provisions of this Act`
  line `(other than for the purpose of giving evidence) that the said person is a child, the Committee or the Board`
  line `shall record such observation stating the age of the child as nearly as may be and proceed with the inquiry`
  line `under section 14 or section 36, as the case may be, without waiting for further confirmation of the age.`
  line
  line `(2) In case, the Committee or the Board has reasonable grounds for doubt regarding whether the`
  line `person brought before it is a child or not, the Committee or the Board, as the case may be, shall undertake`
  line `the process of age determination, by seeking evidence by obtaining—`
  line
  line `(i) the date of birth certificate from the school, or the matriculation or equivalent certificate from`
  line `the concerned examination Board, if available; and in the absence thereof;`
  line
  line `(ii) the birth certificate given by a corporation or a municipal authority or a panchayat;`
  line
  line `(iii) and only in the absence of (i) and (ii) above, age shall be determined by an ossification test or`
  line `any other latest medical age determination test conducted on the orders of the Committee or the`
  line `Board:`
  line
  line `Provided such age determination test conducted on the order of the Committee or the Board shall be`
  line `completed within fifteen days from the date of such order.`
  line
  line `(3) The age recorded by the Committee or the Board to be the age of person so brought before it shall,`
  line `for the purpose of this Act, be deemed to be the true age of that person.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (12815)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Transfer of a child to place of residence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12815&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) If during the inquiry it is found that a child hails`
  line `from a place outside the jurisdiction, the Board or Committee, as the case may be, shall, if satisfied after`
  line `due inquiry that it is in the best interest of the child and after due consultation with the Committee or the`
  line `Board of the childs home district, order the transfer of the child, as soon as possible, to the said`
  line `Committee or the Board, along with relevant documents and following such procedure as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such transfer can be made in case of a child in conflict with law, only after the inquiry`
  line `has been completed and final order passed by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of inter-State transfer, the child shall be, if convenient, handed over to`
  line `the Committee or the Board, as the case may be, of the home district of the child, or to the Committee or`
  line `the Board in the capital city of the home State.`
  line
  line `(2) Once the decision to transfer is finalised, the Committee or Board, as the case may be, shall give`
  line `an escort order to the Special Juvenile Police Unit to escort the child, within fifteen days of receiving such`
  line `order:`
  line
  line `Provided that a girl child shall be accompanied by a woman police officer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where a Special Juvenile Police Unit is not available, the Committee or Board,`
  line `as the case may be, shall direct the institution where the child is temporarily staying or District Child`
  line `Protection Unit, to provide an escort to accompany the child during travel.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall make rules to provide for travelling allowance to the escorting staff`
  line `for the child, which shall be paid in advance.`
  line
  line `(4) The Committee or the Board, as the case may be, receiving the transferred child will process for`
  line `restoration or rehabilitation or social re-integration, as provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (12816)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Transfer of child between Children’s Homes, or special homes or fit facility or fit person in different parts of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12816&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may at any time, on the recommendation of a`
  line `Committee or Board, as the case may be, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, and keeping the`
  line `best interest of the child in mind, order the child's transfer from any Children's Home or special home or`
  line `fit facility or fit person, to a home or facility, within the State with prior intimation to the concerned`
  line `Committee or the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that for transfer of a child between similar home or facility or person within the same`
  line `district, the Committee or Board, as the case may be, of the said district shall be competent to issue such`
  line `an order.`
  line
  line `(2) If transfer is being ordered by a State Government to an institution outside the State, this shall be`
  line `done only in consultation with the concerned State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The total period of stay of the child in a Children's Home or a special home shall not be increased`
  line `by such transfer.`
  line
  line `(4) Orders passed under sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be deemed to be operative for the Committee or`
  line `the Board, as the case may be, of the area to which the child is sent.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (12817)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Release of a child from an institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12817&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a child is kept in a Children's Home or`
  line `special home, on a report of a probation officer or social worker or of Government or a voluntary or nongovernmental`
  line `organisation, as the case may be, the Committee or the Board may consider, the release of`
  line `such child, either absolutely or on such conditions as it may think fit to impose, permitting the child to`
  line `live with parents or guardian or under the supervision of any authorised person named in the order,`
  line `willing to receive and take charge, educate and train the child, for some useful trade or calling or to look`
  line `after the child for rehabilitation:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a child who has been released conditionally under this section, or the person under`
  line `whose supervision the child has been placed, fails to fulfil such conditions, the Board or Committee may,`
  line `if necessary, cause the child to be taken charge of and to be placed back in the concerned home.`
  line
  line `(2) If the child has been released on a temporary basis, the time during which the child is not present`
  line `in the concerned home in pursuance of the permission granted under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be`
  line `part of the time for which the child is liable to be kept in the children or special home:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a child in conflict with law fails to fulfil the conditions set by the Board as`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (1), the time for which he is still liable to be kept in the institution shall be`
  line `extended by the Board for a period equivalent to the time which lapses due to such failure.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (12818)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Leave of absence to a child placed in an institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12818&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee or the Board, as the`
  line `case may be, may permit leave of absence to any child, to allow him, on special occasions like`
  line `examination, marriage of relatives, death of kith or kin or accident or serious illness of parent or any emergency of like nature, under supervision, for a period generally not exceeding seven days in one`
  line `instance, excluding the time taken in journey.`
  line
  line `(2) The time during which a child is absent from an institution where he is placed, in pursuance of`
  line `such permission granted under this section, shall be deemed to be part of the time for which he is liable to`
  line `be kept in the Children's Home or special home.`
  line
  line `(3) If a child refuses, or has failed to return to the Children's Home or special home, as the case may`
  line `be, on the leave period being exhausted or permission being revoked or forfeited, the Board or Committee`
  line `may, if necessary, cause him to be taken charge of and to be taken back to the concerned home:`
  line
  line `Provided that when a child in conflict with law has failed to return to the special home on the leave`
  line `period being exhausted or on permission being revoked or forfeited, the time for which he is still liable to`
  line `be kept in the institution shall be extended by the Board for a period equivalent to the time which lapses`
  line `due to such failure.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (12819)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Reports to be treated as confidential.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12819&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) All reports related to the child and considered by the`
  line `Committee or the Board shall be treated as confidential:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Committee or the Board, as the case may be, may, if it so thinks fit, communicate`
  line `the substance thereof to another Committee or Board or to the child or to the childs parent or guardian,`
  line `and may give such Committee or the Board or the child or parent or guardian, an opportunity of`
  line `producing evidence as may be relevant to the matter stated in the report.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the victim shall not be denied access to their case`
  line `record, orders and relevant papers.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (12820)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12820&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, or the State Government or any person acting under the directions of`
  line `the Central Government or State Government, as the case may be, in respect of anything which is done in`
  line `good faith or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (12821)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12821&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, any person aggrieved by an order made by the Committee or the Board under this Act may, within thirty days from the date of such order, prefer an appeal to the Children's Court, except for decisions by the Committee related to Foster Care and Sponsorship After Care for which the appeal shall lie with the District Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court of Sessions, or the District Magistrate, as the case may be, may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time and such appeal shall be decided within a period of thirty days.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal shall lie against an order of the Board passed after making the preliminary assessment into a heinous offence under section 15 of the Act, before the Court of Sessions and the Court may, while deciding the appeal, take the assistance of experienced psychologists and medical specialists other than those whose assistance has been obtained by the Board in passing the order under the said section.`
  line `^1[(3) No appeal shall lie from any order of acquittal made by the Board in respect of a child alleged to have committed an offence other than the heinous offence by a child who has completed or is above the age of sixteen years.]`
  line
  line `(4) No second appeal shall lie from any order of the Court of Session, passed in appeal under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(5) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Children's Court may file an appeal before the High`
  line `Court in accordance with the procedure specified in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `^2[(6) Any person aggrieved by an adoption order passed by the District Magistrate may, within a period of thirty days from the date of such order passed by the District Magistrate, file an appeal before the Divisional Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(7) Every appeal filed under sub-section (6), shall be decided as expeditiously as possible and an endeavour shall be made to dispose it within a period of four weeks from the date of filing of the appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that where there is no Divisional Commissioner, the State Government or Union territory Administration, as the case may be, may, by notification, empower an officer equivalent to the rank of the Divisional Commissioner to decide the appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 28, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (12822)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title Revision.
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12822&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may, at any time, either on its own motion or on an application`
  line `received in this behalf, call for the record of any proceeding in which any Committee or Board or`
  line `Children's Court, or Court has passed an order, for the purpose of satisfying itself as to the legality or`
  line `propriety of any such order and may pass such order in relation thereto as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court shall not pass an order under this section prejudicial to any person`
  line `without giving him a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (12823)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Procedure in inquiries, appeals and revision proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12823&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly`
  line `provided by this Act, a Committee or a Board while holding any inquiry under any of the provisions of`
  line `this Act, shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed and subject thereto, shall follow, as far as may`
  line `be, the procedure laid down in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) for trial of summons`
  line cases.
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise expressly provided by or under this Act, the procedure to be followed in`
  line `hearing appeals or revision proceedings under this Act shall be, as far as practicable, in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (12824)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Power of the Committee or the Board to amend its own orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12824&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to`
  line `the provisions for appeal and revision contained in this Act, the Committee or the Board may, on an`
  line `application received in this behalf, amend any orders passed by itself, as to the institution to which a child`
  line `is to be sent or as to the person under whose care or supervision a child is to be placed under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that during the course of hearing for amending any such orders, there shall be at least two`
  line `members of the Board of which one shall be the Principal Magistrate and at least three members of the`
  line `Committee and all persons concerned, or their authorised representatives, whose views shall be heard by`
  line `the Committee or the Board, as the case may be, before the said orders are amended.`
  line
  line `(2) Clerical mistakes in orders passed by the Committee or the Board or errors arising therein from`
  line `any accidental slip or omission may, at any time, be corrected by the Committee or the Board, as the case`
  line `may be, either on its own motion or on an application received in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (12825)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Juvenile justice fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12825&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may create a fund in such name as it thinks`
  line `fit for the welfare and rehabilitation of the children dealt with under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be credited to the fund such voluntary donations, contributions or subscriptions as may`
  line `be made by any individual or organisation.`
  line
  line `(3) The fund created under sub-section (1) shall be administered by the Department of the State`
  line `Government implementing this Act in such manner and for such purposes as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (12826)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `State Child Protection Society and District Child Protection Unit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12826&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `Every State Government`
  line `shall constitute a Child Protection Society for the State and Child Protection Unit for every District,`
  line `consisting of such officers and other employees as may be appointed by that Government, to take up`
  line `matters relating to children with a view to ensure the implementation of this Act, including the`
  line `establishment and maintenance of institutions under this Act, notification of competent authorities in`
  line `relation to the children and their rehabilitation and co-ordination with various official and non-official`
  line `agencies concerned and to discharge such other functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (12827)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Child Welfare Police Officer and Special Juvenile Police Unit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12827&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every police station, at`
  line `least one officer, not below the rank of assistant sub-inspector, with aptitude, appropriate training and`
  line `orientation may be designated as the child welfare police officer to exclusively deal with children either`
  line `as victims or perpetrators, in co-ordination with the police, voluntary and non-governmental`
  line organisations.
  line
  line `(2) To co-ordinate all functions of police related to children, the State Government shall constitute`
  line `Special Juvenile Police Units in each district and city, headed by a police officer not below the rank of a`
  line `Deputy Superintendent of Police or above and consisting of all police officers designated under subsection`
  line `(1) and two social workers having experience of working in the field of child welfare, of whom`
  line `one shall be a woman.`
  line
  line `(3) All police officers of the Special Juvenile Police Units shall be provided special training,`
  line `especially at induction as child welfare police officer, to enable them to perform their functions more`
  line effectively.
  line
  line `(4) Special Juvenile Police Unit also includes Railway police dealing with children.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (12828)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Public awareness on provisions of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12828&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government and every State`
  line `Government, shall take necessary measures to ensure that—`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of this Act are given wide publicity through media including television, radio`
  line `and print media at regular intervals so as to make the general public, children and their parents or`
  line `guardians aware of such provisions;`
  line
  line `(b) the officers of the Central Government, State Government and other concerned, persons are`
  line `imparted periodic training on the matters relating to the implementation of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (12829)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Monitoring of implementation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12829&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Commission for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights constituted under section 3, or as the case may be, the State Commission for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights constituted under section 17 (herein referred to as the National Commission or the State`
  line `Commission, as the case may be), of the Commissions for Protection of Child rights Act, 2005`
  line `(4 of 2006), shall, in addition to the functions assigned to them under the said Act, also monitor the`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act, in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Commission or, as the case may be, the State Commission, shall, while inquiring`
  line `into any matter relating to any offence under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in the National`
  line `Commission or the State Commission under the Commissions for Protection of Child Rights Act, 2005 (4`
  line `of 2006).`
  line
  line `(3) The National Commission or, as the case may be, the State Commission, shall also include its`
  line `activities under this section, in the annual report referred to in section 16 of the Commissions for`
  line `Protection of Child Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (12830)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2021, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-9-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12830&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, frame model rules in respect of all or any of the matters`
  line `with respect to which the State Government is required to make rules and where any such model rules`
  line `have been framed in respect of any such matter, they shall apply to the State mutatis mutandis until the`
  line `rules in respect of that matter are made by the State Government and while making any such rules, they`
  line `conform to such model rules.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) manner of inquiry in case of a missing or run away child or whose parents cannot be found`
  line `under sub-clause (vii) of clause (14) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(ii) responsibilities of the Child Welfare Officer attached to a Children's Home under clause (17)`
  line `of section 2;`
  line
  line `(iii) qualifications of the members of the Board under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(iv) induction training and sensitisation of all members of the Board under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(v) term of office of the members of the Board and the manner in which such member may resign`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(vi) time of the meetings of the Board and the rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of`
  line `business at its meeting under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(vii) qualifications, experience and payment of fees of an interpreter or translator under clause (d)`
  line `of sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(viii) any other function of the Board under clause (n) of sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(ix) persons through whom any child alleged to be in conflict with law may be produced before`
  line `the Board and the manner in which such a child may be sent to an observation home or place of safety`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(x) manner in which a person apprehended and not released on bail by the officer-in-charge of the`
  line `police station may be kept in an observation home until such person is brought before a Board under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(xi) format for information on pendency in the Board to the Chief Judicial Magistrate or the Chief`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate and District Magistrate on quarterly basis under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(xii) monitoring procedures and list of monitoring authorities under sub-section (2) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(xiii) manner in which the relevant records of the child may be destroyed by the Board, police or`
  line `the court under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(xiv) qualifications of the members of the Child Welfare Committee under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 27;`
  line
  line `^1[(xiva) the form of report submitted to the District Magistrate under sub-section (8) of Section`
  line 27;]
  line
  line `(xv) rules and procedures with regard to transaction of business at the meetings of the Child`
  line `Welfare Committee under sub-section (1) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(xvi) process of restoration of abandoned or lost children to their families under clause (x) of`
  line `section 30;`
  line
  line `(xvii) manner of submitting the report to the Committee and the manner of sending and entrusting`
  line `the child to Children's Home or fit facility or fit person under sub-section (2) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(xviii) manner of holding an inquiry by the Child Welfare Committee under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 36;`
  line
  line `(xix) manner in which a child may be sent to a Specialised Adoption Agency if the child is below`
  line `six years of age, Children's Home or to a fit facility or person or foster family, till suitable means of`
  line `rehabilitation are found for the child including manner in which situation of the child placed in a`
  line `Children's Home or with a fit facility or person or foster family, may be reviewed by the Committee`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(xx) manner in which a quarterly report may be submitted by the Committee to the District`
  line `Magistrate for review of pendency of cases under sub-section (4) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(xxi) any other order related to any other function of the Committee under clause (iii) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(xxii) information to be given every month by the Committee to State Agency and Authority`
  line `regarding number of children declared legally free for adoption and number of cases pending under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 38;`
  line
  line `^1[(xxiia) the form of quarterly report regarding restored, dead and runaway children under`
  line `sub-section (4) of Section 40;]`
  line
  line `(xxiii) manner in which all institutions under this Act shall be registered under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 41;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) procedure for cancelling or withholding registration of an institution that fails to provide`
  line `rehabilitation and re-integration services under sub-section (7) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(xxv) manner in which information shall be sent every month by the open shelter to the District`
  line `Child Protection Unit and Committee under sub-section (3) of section 43;`
  line
  line `(xxvi) procedure for placing children in foster care including group foster care under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) procedure for inspection of children in foster care under sub-section (4) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(xxviii) manner in which foster family shall provide education, health and nutrition to the child`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(xxix) procedure and criteria in which foster care services shall be provided to children under subsection (7) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(xxx) format for inspection of foster families by the Committee to check the well being of`
  line `children under sub-section (8) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(xxxi) purpose of undertaking various programmes of sponsorship of children, such as individual`
  line `to individual sponsorship, group sponsorship or community sponsorship under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 45;`
  line
  line `(xxxii) duration of sponsorship under sub-section (3) of section 45;`
  line
  line `(xxxiii) manner of providing financial support to any child leaving institutional care on`
  line `completing eighteen years of age under section 46;`
  line
  line `(xxxiv) management and monitoring of observation homes, including the standards and various`
  line `types of services to be provided by them for rehabilitation and social integration of a child alleged to`
  line `be in conflict with law and the circumstances under which, and the manner in which, the registration`
  line `of an observation home may be granted or withdrawn under sub-section (3) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(xxxv) management and monitoring of special homes including the standards and various types of`
  line `services to be provided to them under sub-section (2) and sub-section (3) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(xxxvi) monitoring and management of children's homes including the standards and the nature of`
  line `services to be provided by them, based on individual care plans for each child under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 50;`
  line
  line `(xxxvii) manner in which a Board or the Committee shall recognise, a facility being run by a`
  line `Governmental organisation or a voluntary or non-governmental organisation registered under any law`
  line `for the time being in force, fit to temporarily take the responsibility of a child for a specific purpose`
  line `after due inquiry regarding the suitability of the facility and the organisation to take care of the child`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(xxxviii) procedure of verification of credentials, for recognising any person fit to temporarily`
  line `receive a child for care, protection and treatment of such child for a specified period by the Board or`
  line `the Committee under sub-section (1) of section 52;`
  line
  line `(xxxix) manner in which services shall be provided by an institution under this Act for`
  line `rehabilitation and re-integration of children and standards for basic requirements such as food, shelter,`
  line `clothing and medical attention under sub-section (1) of section 53;`
  line
  line `(xl) manner in which Management Committee shall be set up by each institution for management`
  line `of the institution and monitoring of the progress of every child under sub-section (2) of section 53;`
  line
  line `(xli) activities that may be taken up by children's committees under sub-section (3) of section 53;`
  line
  line `(xlii) appointment of inspection committees for all institutions registered or recognised fit, for the`
  line `State and district under sub-section (1) of section 54;`
  line
  line `(xliii) manner in which Central Government or State Government may independently evaluate the`
  line `functioning of the Board, Committee, special juvenile police units, registered institutions, or`
  line `recognised fit facilities and persons, including the period and through persons or institutions under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 55;`
  line
  line `(xliv) manner in which institutions shall furnish details of children declared legally free for`
  line `adoption to the Specialised Adoption Agency under sub-section (2) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(xlv) any other function of the Authority under clause (e) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(xlvi) criteria for the selection or nomination of the Members of the Steering Committee of the`
  line `Authority and their tenure as well as the terms and conditions of their appointment under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 69;`
  line
  line `(xlvii) manner in which Steering Committee of the Authority shall meet under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 69;`
  line
  line `(xlviii) manner in which the Authority shall submit an annual report to the Central Government`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 71;`
  line
  line `(xlix) functions of the Authority under sub-section (2) of section 72;`
  line
  line `(l) manner in which the Authority shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records and`
  line `prepare an annual statement of accounts under sub-section (1) of section 73;`
  line
  line `(li) period that the Committee or Board may think necessary for the treatment of children who are`
  line `found to be suffering from a disease requiring prolonged medical treatment or physical or mental`
  line `complaint that will respond to treatment to a fit facility under section 92;`
  line
  line `(lii) procedure for transfer of child under sub-section (1) of section 95;`
  line
  line `(liii) provision for travelling allowance to the escorting staff for the child under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 95;`
  line
  line `(liv) procedure to be followed by the Committee or a Board while holding any inquiry, appeal or`
  line `revision under sub-section (1) of section 103;`
  line
  line `(lv) manner in which juvenile justice fund shall be administered under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 105;`
  line
  line `(lvi) functioning of the Child Protection Society for the State and Child Protection Units for every`
  line `district under section 106;`
  line
  line `(lvii) to enable the National Commission, or as the case may be, the State Commission to monitor`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act under sub-section (1) of section 109;`
  line
  line `(lviii) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule and every regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made,`
  line `the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (12831)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12831&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2000`
  line `(56 of 2000) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Acts shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (12832)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168&sectionId=12832&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_000010_201602_1517807328168
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of the period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) However, order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
